♪ You know I can be found

00:08.476 --> 00:11.310
♪ Sittin' home all alone

00:11.345 --> 00:13.979
♪ If you can't come around

00:14.015 --> 00:16.482
♪ At least please telephone

00:16.517 --> 00:21.754
♪ Don't be cruel to
a heart that's true ♪

00:22.723 --> 00:25.424
♪ Baby if I made you mad

00:25.459 --> 00:28.460
♪ With something I
might have said ♪

00:28.496 --> 00:30.929
♪ Please forget my past

00:30.965 --> 00:33.599
♪ The future looks
bright ahead ♪

00:33.634 --> 00:38.804
♪ Don't be cruel to
a heart that's true ♪

00:39.573 --> 00:42.608
♪ I don't want no other love

00:42.643 --> 00:47.813
♪ I really love you
baby cross my heart ♪

00:48.582 --> 00:51.050
♪ Let's walk to the preacher

00:51.085 --> 00:53.952
♪ And let's say I do

00:53.988 --> 00:56.522
♪ Then you'll know you have me

00:56.557 --> 00:58.991
♪ And I know that
I'll have you ♪

00:59.026 --> 01:04.263
♪ Don't be cruel to
a heart that's true ♪

01:04.932 --> 01:07.966
♪ I don't want no other love

01:08.002 --> 01:08.834
- We're gonna be late mom.

01:08.903 --> 01:10.969
What if the carpool
leaves without us?

01:11.005 --> 01:13.005
- Emma honey, I think
we're gonna be okay.

01:13.040 --> 01:14.540
Back me up Sal, we good?

01:14.575 --> 01:15.974
- Right on time.

01:16.010 --> 01:16.942
Can't have these two
running late just because

01:16.977 --> 01:20.045
summer break is only
two weeks away, right?

01:20.081 --> 01:21.413
- Now, is a goodbye
kiss still okay,

01:21.449 --> 01:22.848
or are you girls getting
too big for that?

01:22.883 --> 01:25.050
- We're only to big
for it at school.

01:25.086 --> 01:26.585
- And now we know.

01:27.922 --> 01:29.721
All right, y'all have
a great day, sweetie.

01:29.757 --> 01:32.691
Clay's set to pick you up
after, so look for him, okay?

01:32.726 --> 01:33.959
And I'll see ya later?

01:33.994 --> 01:36.295
- [Both] You sure will.

01:36.330 --> 01:39.064
- What's that all about?

01:39.100 --> 01:40.099
Is something up?

01:40.134 --> 01:41.567
- Why would something be up?

01:41.602 --> 01:42.835
And shouldn't you
be at work by now?

01:42.870 --> 01:44.169
- I'm going, I'm going.

01:44.205 --> 01:45.571
- Okay.
- Bye y'all.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.039
- Bye.

01:47.074 --> 01:50.142
(gentle guitar music)

01:54.548 --> 01:55.781
- Big day, Laurel.

01:55.816 --> 01:57.015
Everything on track?

01:57.051 --> 01:59.017
- Just finishing up
your speech, sir.

01:59.053 --> 02:00.853
- Outstanding, how do I sound?

02:00.888 --> 02:03.655
- Brilliant,
sincere, and modest.

02:03.691 --> 02:06.725
- All my best
qualities (chuckles).

02:06.760 --> 02:08.861
But seriously, thank you.

02:08.896 --> 02:10.395
You know, hiring you
away from Chicago

02:10.431 --> 02:13.966
was one of the best
decisions I ever made.

02:14.001 --> 02:15.400
Is Clay coming to the ceremony?

02:15.436 --> 02:16.969
It's been a while
since I've seen him.

02:17.004 --> 02:18.270
- Well, if he can get away.

02:18.305 --> 02:20.105
You know Clay and
his work schedule,

02:20.141 --> 02:22.241
definitely not bankers' hours.

02:22.276 --> 02:24.309
- Oh, carry on.

02:24.345 --> 02:27.980
(peaceful chiming music)

02:30.384 --> 02:32.217
- Okay, well the venue
has to hold 3,000.

02:32.253 --> 02:35.821
On my night, it was five, will
you check its availability?

02:35.856 --> 02:36.722
Thank you.

02:37.958 --> 02:40.392
All right, well tell them it's
me, they might cut us a deal.

02:40.427 --> 02:42.761
Back-up singers, dancers.

02:42.796 --> 02:46.999
Yeah, yeah no, I'll see you
in New Orleans next month.

02:47.034 --> 02:49.067
Yeah, well I'll eat next week.

02:49.103 --> 02:52.738
All right, Ed I gotta go man,
my biggest star's waiting.

02:52.773 --> 02:55.974
- This new branch of
Cypress Savings and Loan

02:56.010 --> 02:57.209
wouldn't have been possible

02:57.244 --> 03:00.045
without the support of
our entire community,

03:00.080 --> 03:02.548
which is all of you, so
give yourselves a hand.

03:02.583 --> 03:05.384
(audience applauding)

03:05.419 --> 03:08.086
And as with each new
branch that we open,

03:08.122 --> 03:10.989
it isn't really official until
we plant a cypress sapling

03:11.025 --> 03:14.493
grown from the original
cypress that my grandpa grew

03:14.528 --> 03:17.462
on our family farm
over 80 years ago.

03:17.498 --> 03:18.297
- Wow.

03:18.332 --> 03:19.965
- And for all her hard work,

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
the honor of
planting this sapling

03:22.036 --> 03:25.170
really should go
to Laurel Couper.

03:25.206 --> 03:25.871
- Me, sir?

03:25.906 --> 03:27.139
- Everyone, won't you join me

03:27.174 --> 03:29.007
in thanking our
newest vice president,

03:29.043 --> 03:31.310
who almost single handedly

03:31.345 --> 03:34.413
made this newest branch
a reality, Laurel Couper.

03:34.448 --> 03:36.548
(audience applauding)
- That wasn't in the speech.

03:36.584 --> 03:38.217
- Go right ahead.

03:39.086 --> 03:41.954
- Well, I am, ah,
practically speechless,

03:41.989 --> 03:44.489
and those of you who know
me know how rare that is.

03:44.525 --> 03:45.224
- Yes.

03:45.259 --> 03:46.525
(audience laughing)

03:46.560 --> 03:48.227
- Let me just say
that I am so proud

03:48.262 --> 03:51.763
to be even a small part of this.

03:51.799 --> 03:52.798
You really want me to?

03:52.833 --> 03:53.632
- Yes.

03:54.501 --> 03:56.501
- All right, here goes.

03:58.973 --> 04:00.172
Declare this latest branch

04:00.207 --> 04:03.742
of Cypress Savings and
Loan officially open.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.944
(audience cheering
and applauding)

04:05.980 --> 04:06.845
Thank you.

04:08.682 --> 04:10.949
Well, look who showed up.

04:10.985 --> 04:12.417
- You did such a
good job, mommy.

04:12.453 --> 04:14.319
- Thank you, baby.

04:14.355 --> 04:17.256
I love looking out in the
crowd and seeing you two.

04:17.291 --> 04:18.190
- Can I take my two girls out

04:18.259 --> 04:19.891
for a little dinner
tonight and celebrate?

04:19.927 --> 04:20.592
- Yeah.

04:20.628 --> 04:21.693
- [Clay] Pick you up at seven?

04:21.729 --> 04:23.528
- Sounds like a plan.

04:25.866 --> 04:27.165
- All right, I know we're
running a little bit late.

04:27.201 --> 04:28.934
You guys mind if we
stop at Graceland?

04:28.969 --> 04:30.102
I have some papers
I need to give them

04:30.137 --> 04:31.169
for an event next week.

04:31.205 --> 04:32.237
- Oh.

04:32.273 --> 04:34.640
- Oh, we don't mind, do we mom?

04:34.675 --> 04:36.174
- Of course not.

04:37.077 --> 04:40.679
(whimsical woodwind music)

04:45.953 --> 04:49.054
- [Emma] Did you know Elvis
was his daddy's middle name?

04:49.089 --> 04:49.988
I heard that in school.

04:50.024 --> 04:51.290
- [Laurel] Is that what
they're teaching you

04:51.325 --> 04:52.891
in music class these days?

04:52.926 --> 04:55.594
- [Clay] All right,
ladies, here we are.

04:55.629 --> 04:57.229
(car door shuts)

04:57.264 --> 04:58.997
Back in a flash.

04:59.033 --> 05:00.732
- Do you know what I like
best about Graceland?

05:00.768 --> 05:01.900
- What?

05:01.935 --> 05:03.468
- It's where we met
Clay last Christmas.

05:03.504 --> 05:07.539
- That's right, what a
holiday treat that was.

05:09.109 --> 05:12.177
(light guitar music)

05:12.212 --> 05:17.416
♪ Love me tender,
love me sweet ♪

05:19.219 --> 05:21.720
♪ Never let me go

05:21.755 --> 05:24.523
- You know, seeing you
here last Christmas

05:24.558 --> 05:27.159
was one of the best
days of my life.

05:27.194 --> 05:29.361
It started right here.

05:32.032 --> 05:33.799
Actually, you know
what, that's not true.

05:33.834 --> 05:36.768
It started when you
came and sat next to me

05:36.804 --> 05:39.071
in Miss Miller's
third grade class.

05:39.106 --> 05:44.109
- Okay, you two have been acting
strange all day, what's up?

05:44.144 --> 05:45.143
- Clay?
- Yeah.

05:45.245 --> 05:47.079
- Get to the point.
- Right, right, right, right.

05:47.114 --> 05:51.450
The point is, the point is
I lost you once already.

05:53.220 --> 05:56.221
I'm not gonna ever
lose you again.

05:56.256 --> 05:59.157
You know how much I love you.

05:59.193 --> 06:02.227
You know how much I love Emma.

06:02.262 --> 06:04.196
So, Laurel Couper.

06:04.231 --> 06:08.300
♪ Love me tender, love me long

06:10.104 --> 06:11.803
- Will you marry me?

06:12.873 --> 06:13.739
- Will I?

06:15.042 --> 06:17.175
- Will I is not an answer,
it's actually a question.

06:17.211 --> 06:20.212
- Yes, it is, of
course, yes, yes!

06:21.115 --> 06:24.616
(Laurel giggling)
- It fits.

06:25.786 --> 06:27.319
- She said yes!

06:27.354 --> 06:28.086
- Oh, my goodness.

06:28.122 --> 06:30.756
- (screams) Oh, my gosh!

06:30.791 --> 06:33.825
(laughing loudly) Congrats!

06:33.861 --> 06:35.227
- Congratulations, buddy.
- Thank you, bud.

06:35.262 --> 06:36.795
- [Sally] Oh, my goodness!

06:36.830 --> 06:39.698
- Were you all in on this?

06:39.733 --> 06:40.932
- About time.

06:40.968 --> 06:42.434
- Oh, my gosh.

06:42.469 --> 06:43.702
- Thank you, baby.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.103
- Oh, let me see, let me see.

06:45.139 --> 06:46.405
- Oh, look.
- Nice.

06:46.440 --> 06:49.241
- That is the most
beautiful thing I have seen

06:49.276 --> 06:50.575
since Ted proposed to me.

06:50.611 --> 06:51.276
- Oh, you.

06:51.311 --> 06:52.344
- Almost like a real diamond.

06:52.379 --> 06:53.311
(all chuckling)

06:53.347 --> 06:54.479
- [Ted] Oh, this guy.

06:54.548 --> 06:58.350
- And you, mister, how long
have you been planning this?

06:58.385 --> 07:02.120
- From the moment I
saw you last Christmas.

07:03.724 --> 07:05.524
- There's a wedding!

07:05.559 --> 07:07.459
There's so much to
do, so much to plan.

07:07.494 --> 07:11.730
- Starting with where are
you guys gonna get married?

07:11.765 --> 07:13.598
- I think there's
only one place.

07:13.634 --> 07:14.699
- [Laurel And Clay]
Graceland Chapel.

07:14.735 --> 07:15.967
- [Ted] All right.

07:16.003 --> 07:17.502
- Oh my God, yeah!

07:19.306 --> 07:20.405
- Love you.
- I love you.

07:20.474 --> 07:23.608
- So, when are you gonna
tell your folks the big news?

07:23.644 --> 07:25.911
- [Laurel And Clay] Our folks.

07:25.946 --> 07:28.213
(computer beeping)

07:28.248 --> 07:28.914
- [Clay] Hey, Dad.

07:28.949 --> 07:30.615
- [Tyler] Clay, what's wrong?

07:30.651 --> 07:31.850
It's late, something's wrong.

07:31.885 --> 07:32.984
- [Clay] Nothing's wrong.

07:33.020 --> 07:34.286
- Trish, something's wrong.
- Dad?

07:34.321 --> 07:35.153
Nothing's wrong, it's
actually the opposite.

07:35.189 --> 07:35.887
Laurel and I--

07:35.923 --> 07:36.922
- [Trish] Give me that.

07:36.957 --> 07:38.857
Hey, Clay, it's your mama.

07:38.892 --> 07:40.091
- I know, I can see you.

07:40.127 --> 07:41.726
- [Trish] You and Laurel what?

07:41.762 --> 07:44.029
- Laurel and I are, well.

07:45.833 --> 07:47.532
We're getting married.

07:47.568 --> 07:49.367
- [Trish] Oh (giggling)!

07:49.403 --> 07:51.470
(screams) Oh, they're
getting married, Tyler!

07:51.505 --> 07:52.304
They're getting married!

07:52.406 --> 07:54.306
- [Tyler] I can
hear. I'm right here.

07:54.341 --> 07:55.674
- Hey, Mrs. Sheppard, it's true!

07:55.709 --> 07:56.875
(Laurel and Trish screaming)

07:56.910 --> 07:58.543
- [Tyler] Hey, Clay,
congratulations.

07:58.579 --> 07:59.377
Way to go, pal.

07:59.446 --> 08:02.714
- [Trish] Oh, honey,
I'm so excited.

08:02.749 --> 08:04.282
We gotta hang up, we
gotta call the family.

08:04.318 --> 08:05.617
How do you make it--
- Wait, wait, wait, Mom?

08:05.652 --> 08:06.852
- [Trish] Make it?
(phone beeping)

08:06.887 --> 08:09.488
- Mom?
(Laurel chuckling)

08:09.523 --> 08:11.690
Okay, bye, that was a good talk.

08:11.725 --> 08:14.226
- Well, they're excited.

08:14.261 --> 08:15.160
Your turn?

08:16.363 --> 08:18.196
- Oh okay, here goes.

08:21.168 --> 08:24.202
(computer beeping)

08:24.972 --> 08:26.505
Hello, daddy?

08:26.540 --> 08:29.074
- [Laurel's Dad] Hey sweetheart,
how's the bank opening go?

08:29.109 --> 08:30.275
- Oh, it was great.

08:30.310 --> 08:34.346
Mr. Franklin actually had me
plant the tree, well partially.

08:34.381 --> 08:35.514
I'll send you a photo.

08:35.549 --> 08:38.016
I have got some big news.

08:38.051 --> 08:39.384
- [Laurel's Dad] I'm listening.

08:39.419 --> 08:43.255
- So, Clay and I, we've
been making some plans.

08:43.290 --> 08:44.756
- [Laurel's Dad] I hope
you're not planning

08:44.791 --> 08:45.991
to go on the road again.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.059
You just got this new
position at the bank.

08:48.095 --> 08:50.462
- No, daddy, we're
not going on tour.

08:50.497 --> 08:51.897
Different news.

08:51.932 --> 08:56.434
So, Clay proposed and we're
getting married (shrieks).

08:56.470 --> 08:59.571
- [Laurel's Dad]
Well, that is news.

08:59.606 --> 09:02.474
Congratulations, honey.

09:02.509 --> 09:03.909
That's just fine.

09:05.379 --> 09:06.578
- Fine?

09:06.613 --> 09:09.948
- [Laurel's Dad]
Really, really fine.

09:13.820 --> 09:16.187
- [Laurel] I can't believe
we're actually getting married.

09:16.223 --> 09:17.389
My head's still spinning.

09:17.424 --> 09:19.958
- Laurel Couper, you're not
having second thoughts, are you?

09:19.993 --> 09:21.426
- Goodness, no.

09:22.629 --> 09:24.462
Just taking it all in.

09:24.498 --> 09:27.699
I do wish my dad would've
been a little bit more--

09:27.734 --> 09:28.667
- Excited for us?

09:28.702 --> 09:30.268
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

09:30.304 --> 09:32.404
- Well, we did kind of
spring it on him, so.

09:32.439 --> 09:33.939
- We took your
parents by surprise,

09:33.974 --> 09:36.641
and they did everything
but call the local news.

09:36.677 --> 09:39.277
- I wouldn't put it past them.

09:39.313 --> 09:42.280
Listen, your dad's
gonna come around, okay.

09:42.316 --> 09:44.082
Especially when he
sees how happy you are.

09:44.117 --> 09:45.450
- You're right, you're right.

09:45.485 --> 09:46.451
- I am right.

09:46.486 --> 09:48.286
- I'm overthinking this.

09:48.322 --> 09:51.623
It has to be here, I mean,
Graceland's our good luck charm.

09:51.658 --> 09:52.457
- Yes it is.

09:52.492 --> 09:54.426
- Laurel Couper.

09:54.461 --> 09:55.126
- Hey.

09:55.162 --> 09:57.829
- It's so good to see you both.

09:58.732 --> 10:00.799
Hey Clay.
- How are you?

10:01.835 --> 10:03.468
- Congratulations
on your promotion.

10:03.503 --> 10:04.903
- Thank you.

10:04.938 --> 10:07.639
I'm now the official events
coordinator at Graceland.

10:07.674 --> 10:08.640
- That's fantastic.

10:08.675 --> 10:10.709
- So, you're tying the knot.

10:10.744 --> 10:12.410
- We sure are.

10:12.446 --> 10:14.145
- When I got the message,
I checked our books,

10:14.181 --> 10:18.016
and there is an availability,
- Yeah?

10:18.051 --> 10:19.517
- A year from August.

10:19.553 --> 10:20.919
- Oh, a year.

10:20.954 --> 10:23.722
- As you can imagine, we
have to book way in advance.

10:23.757 --> 10:26.257
Everyone wants to get
married at Graceland.

10:26.293 --> 10:28.760
But if you don't need
that much time to plan,

10:28.795 --> 10:30.395
we just had a cancellation.

10:30.430 --> 10:31.997
There's an opening June 1st.

10:32.032 --> 10:33.698
- I've always dreamed
of a June wedding.

10:33.734 --> 10:34.899
- Yeah.

10:34.935 --> 10:36.267
- That still means
waiting a year.

10:36.303 --> 10:38.403
- No, no, no, no,
no, this June 1st.

10:38.438 --> 10:40.805
- Oh, three weeks from
now, that June 1st?

10:40.841 --> 10:42.140
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh.

10:42.175 --> 10:43.975
Hmm.
- That's amazing.

10:44.778 --> 10:46.378
- And soon.
- Yeah.

10:46.413 --> 10:47.979
- Oh, I'm sorry.

10:48.015 --> 10:48.980
This will be real quick.

10:49.016 --> 10:49.948
Go on, take a look inside.

10:49.983 --> 10:51.683
- Okay.
- Thank you.

10:52.653 --> 10:53.585
- June 1st?

10:56.356 --> 10:59.090
Well, this sure is what we want.

10:59.926 --> 11:01.292
Wow, three weeks.

11:01.328 --> 11:04.029
- Yeah, is that enough
time to pull this off?

11:04.064 --> 11:06.498
- We can keep things simple.

11:06.533 --> 11:09.300
You know, just family, friends.

11:09.336 --> 11:11.970
I don't need anything fancy.

11:12.005 --> 11:15.073
Besides, you know what they say.

11:15.108 --> 11:17.876
- That depends on who "they" is.

11:17.911 --> 11:20.445
- Well, Elvis for one.

11:20.480 --> 11:21.946
It's now or never.

11:23.550 --> 11:25.850
- Can I assume that's a yes?

11:28.422 --> 11:31.623
- And it's set back in the
woods with big glass windows,

11:31.658 --> 11:33.391
so you can see outside.

11:33.427 --> 11:36.661
It's just the cutest
little chapel ever.

11:36.697 --> 11:38.596
How are you feeling
about all this?

11:38.632 --> 11:39.764
- Amazing.

11:39.800 --> 11:41.566
You know, the best part is?
- What?

11:41.601 --> 11:43.601
- Instead of Clay coming
over Sunday mornings

11:43.637 --> 11:47.338
to make pecan pancakes,
he'll make them everyday.

11:47.374 --> 11:49.107
- Well, I'm not
sure about everyday,

11:49.142 --> 11:50.241
but we will definitely
have to come up

11:50.277 --> 11:52.711
with our own little family
traditions like that too.

11:52.746 --> 11:55.513
- Like, family dinners
together every night?

11:55.549 --> 11:59.384
- And more music in this
house if that's even possible.

11:59.419 --> 12:00.652
Now, there's gonna be
a whole lot of planning

12:00.687 --> 12:02.587
to do for the wedding.

12:02.622 --> 12:04.556
Flowers to choose,
cakes to taste.

12:04.591 --> 12:06.324
- Mmm.
- Dresses to pick out.

12:06.359 --> 12:09.227
And I'm gonna need your
advice every step of the way.

12:09.262 --> 12:10.228
Are you up for it?

12:10.263 --> 12:12.197
- Of course, mom, I can't wait.

12:12.232 --> 12:13.231
- Well, you won't
have to wait long,

12:13.266 --> 12:14.966
it's only three weeks away.

12:15.001 --> 12:17.235
Which reminds me, I
need to make a call.

12:17.270 --> 12:18.870
- I love you, mommy, you know.

12:18.905 --> 12:21.406
- I love you too, you know.

12:22.342 --> 12:24.776
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, hon.

12:26.847 --> 12:28.513
- [Laurel's Dad] But don't you
think it's a little rushed?

12:28.548 --> 12:30.982
I mean, you've only been
back in Memphis five months.

12:31.017 --> 12:32.784
- Well, it's only time that
we could get the chapel

12:32.819 --> 12:34.686
without having to wait a year.

12:34.721 --> 12:36.988
- It's a very popular
place to get married.

12:37.023 --> 12:38.823
Daddy, I've known Clay
since we were kids.

12:38.859 --> 12:41.593
If anything, we've taken
slower than molasses.

12:41.628 --> 12:44.896
- But, a June wedding?
- June? That's awfully quick.

12:44.931 --> 12:46.064
- That's why I'm telling you now

12:46.099 --> 12:48.066
so that you and
Isabelle can make plans.

12:48.101 --> 12:50.702
There's no way that I'm
doing this without y'all.

12:50.737 --> 12:53.104
- Now you know the only
thing that I've ever wanted

12:53.140 --> 12:54.372
is what's best for you.

12:54.407 --> 12:56.908
And if you believe that
that's Clay Sheppard--

12:56.943 --> 12:57.776
- It is.

12:59.179 --> 13:00.578
- Then we'll be there.

13:00.614 --> 13:02.213
- That's all I needed to hear.

13:02.249 --> 13:05.450
All right, I gotta go, I have
a wedding to pull together.

13:05.485 --> 13:07.752
I love you, daddy.
- I love you.

13:07.788 --> 13:08.653
Bye.

13:12.826 --> 13:16.828
- So, here are some ideas
I have for the invitations.

13:16.863 --> 13:18.363
- Classy.

13:18.398 --> 13:19.130
Fun.

13:19.166 --> 13:20.765
(chuckling)

13:20.801 --> 13:22.667
Is that a catfish in a tux?

13:22.702 --> 13:23.902
- Ignore that, I was
just playing around.

13:23.937 --> 13:29.474
But, I do have the Save the
Date email and the invitation.

13:30.343 --> 13:31.676
- These are so great,
I love them all.

13:31.711 --> 13:32.477
- Thank you.

13:32.512 --> 13:34.145
- Well, except
maybe the catfish.

13:34.181 --> 13:36.748
Seriously, don't go crazy if
you've got other work to do.

13:36.783 --> 13:38.650
- Are you kidding me,
for my best friend?

13:38.685 --> 13:40.218
Look, try and stop me.

13:40.253 --> 13:42.921
And besides, I work
well under pressure.

13:42.956 --> 13:46.224
(phone dinging)

13:46.259 --> 13:47.325
- What?

13:47.360 --> 13:48.827
- Everything okay?

13:48.862 --> 13:51.696
- My dad just sent me
his flight information.

13:51.731 --> 13:53.565
Him and Isabelle
are coming in early.

13:53.600 --> 13:54.499
- How early?

13:54.534 --> 13:56.634
- The day after tomorrow early.

13:56.670 --> 14:00.839
- Well, I hope you work
well under pressure, too.

14:02.642 --> 14:05.043
- These are great.
- Aren't they?

14:05.078 --> 14:06.511
- [Clay] Yeah,
especially like this one.

14:06.546 --> 14:07.478
- I also booked a
couple of suites

14:07.514 --> 14:10.215
at the Graceland Guest
House for our folks.

14:10.250 --> 14:12.283
Right across the
hall from each other.

14:12.319 --> 14:14.652
- Thank you very much
for taking care of that.

14:14.688 --> 14:17.222
Okay, well, I love
these, fantastic.

14:17.257 --> 14:19.891
- Not a catfish on any of them.

14:19.926 --> 14:21.559
Private joke.

14:21.595 --> 14:23.828
- Well, oh so tomorrow
after sound check,

14:23.864 --> 14:24.963
we should get our
marriage license,

14:25.065 --> 14:29.000
and we still need a minister,
a band for the reception.

14:29.035 --> 14:31.436
The caterer, I made
a little to-do list.

14:31.471 --> 14:32.537
- Is that all?

14:32.572 --> 14:35.874
- Good morning, can I get
you something to drink?

14:35.909 --> 14:37.108
- Sweet tea for me, please.

14:37.143 --> 14:39.611
- And I'll have the
same as my fiance.

14:39.646 --> 14:41.479
- Two fiance specials coming up.

14:41.514 --> 14:44.148
And congratulations,
when's the big day?

14:44.184 --> 14:45.884
- June 1st.

14:45.919 --> 14:47.252
- Just around the corner.

14:47.287 --> 14:48.820
How do you two look so relaxed?

14:48.855 --> 14:51.956
- Would you believe we
just started planning?

14:51.992 --> 14:53.091
- Just started?

14:53.126 --> 14:54.726
Well, honey, you
let me know if I can

14:54.761 --> 14:56.160
get you anything stronger.

14:56.196 --> 14:57.595
- Thank you.

14:57.631 --> 15:00.832
So, how is the concert in
New Orleans shaping up?

15:00.867 --> 15:02.867
- Typical issues,
nothing I can't fix.

15:02.903 --> 15:04.469
Fortunately, we have
a little bit of time

15:04.504 --> 15:07.071
before the relatives get here.

15:08.241 --> 15:11.242
- About that, my
dad and Isabelle,

15:12.345 --> 15:14.846
they're flying in
early to "help."

15:14.881 --> 15:16.981
- Okay, but not next week?

15:17.017 --> 15:18.683
- Oh no, no, no.

15:18.718 --> 15:20.919
More like the day
after tomorrow.

15:20.954 --> 15:23.021
He thinks we need
all hands on deck,

15:23.056 --> 15:25.890
so I figured we should
probably invite your parents

15:25.926 --> 15:27.825
to come in too.

15:27.861 --> 15:28.893
- Are you sure?

15:28.929 --> 15:31.095
- Well yeah, I don't want
them to feel excluded.

15:31.131 --> 15:32.664
Plus, your mom already
thinks I'm the girl

15:32.699 --> 15:34.766
that broke her son's
heart 10 years ago.

15:34.801 --> 15:36.734
- And your dad still thinks
I sing on street corners

15:36.770 --> 15:38.703
with an opened guitar case.

15:38.738 --> 15:40.738
- He's just not
that big on music.

15:40.774 --> 15:42.173
- Well, your dad is who he is.

15:42.208 --> 15:44.342
I remember when I would pick
you up on dates in high school,

15:44.377 --> 15:46.477
he would make me file
in line like I was under

15:46.513 --> 15:48.713
some kind of inspection.

15:48.748 --> 15:51.149
- Well, he's not called
the Major for nothing.

15:51.184 --> 15:52.116
- Well, maybe he's mellowed out.

15:52.152 --> 15:53.618
Wait, what's your stepmom like?

15:53.653 --> 15:54.719
- Isabelle?
- Mm-hmm.

15:54.788 --> 15:58.823
- She's refined, traditional,
a little intimidating.

15:58.858 --> 16:01.826
- Okay, so she and
my mom would be like,

16:01.861 --> 16:03.161
what would you say?

16:03.196 --> 16:05.630
- Oil and water?
- Oh.

16:05.665 --> 16:07.732
- You hear that?
- No, what?

16:07.767 --> 16:12.170
- The sound of two runaway
trains headed our way.

16:17.210 --> 16:19.310
- Young lady, there seems
to be a little mix up,

16:19.346 --> 16:21.312
there's a piano in our room.

16:21.348 --> 16:22.347
- Yes.

16:22.382 --> 16:23.815
- We don't play.

16:23.850 --> 16:25.717
- Sir, that's part
of the luxury suite.

16:25.752 --> 16:26.451
- Oh.

16:26.486 --> 16:28.019
- Daddy, Isabelle.

16:28.054 --> 16:29.487
- There they are.

16:31.324 --> 16:32.690
- Good to see you.

16:32.726 --> 16:34.959
- This cannot be Emma.

16:34.995 --> 16:36.127
- It's me, grandpa.

16:36.162 --> 16:38.930
- You are so big, look at you.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.532
- Mr. Couper, good
to see you, sir.

16:41.568 --> 16:43.334
- Oh, you don't have
to call me, Mr. Couper.

16:43.370 --> 16:44.035
- No?

16:44.070 --> 16:46.537
- The Major will do just fine.

16:46.573 --> 16:49.240
Emma, we got a present for you.

16:51.077 --> 16:52.176
- Nice.

16:53.446 --> 16:55.513
- Whoa, a savings bond.

16:56.983 --> 17:00.385
- Never too soon to start
preparing for your future.

17:00.420 --> 17:02.120
Who knows, maybe
someday you'll follow

17:02.155 --> 17:03.888
in your mom's footsteps.

17:03.923 --> 17:05.189
- And be a singer too?

17:05.225 --> 17:08.760
- I meant the vice
president of a bank.

17:08.795 --> 17:12.397
- Thank you, I really,
really like it.

17:12.432 --> 17:15.867
- Hey, treat her gentle,
she's been through a lot.

17:15.902 --> 17:18.002
Talking about the
car, not the wife.

17:18.038 --> 17:19.904
- He makes that joke every time.

17:19.939 --> 17:22.840
- Never gets old.
- And neither do I.

17:22.876 --> 17:25.043
- Mom.
- Hiya, honey.

17:25.078 --> 17:26.844
- Well, well, welcoming party.

17:26.880 --> 17:27.912
What, no balloons?

17:27.947 --> 17:28.846
Laurel.
- Hey.

17:28.915 --> 17:31.249
- Great to have you
home where you belong.

17:31.284 --> 17:33.818
- Well you know what they say,
"Home is where the heart is."

17:33.853 --> 17:34.519
- Well, let's just
hope your heart

17:34.554 --> 17:37.221
stays here for good this time.

17:38.658 --> 17:40.992
- Tyler and Trish, this
is my father, the Major,

17:41.027 --> 17:42.693
and my stepmother, Isabelle.

17:42.729 --> 17:46.030
- Well hey, Major is
that a name or a rank?

17:46.066 --> 17:47.565
- Both, these days.

17:47.600 --> 17:49.033
- And this is my daughter, Emma.

17:49.069 --> 17:50.968
- Emma, come here, I'm a hugger.

17:51.004 --> 17:53.538
Oh, aren't you just
the prettiest thing.

17:53.573 --> 17:54.405
- Thank you, ma'am.

17:54.441 --> 17:55.306
- Ma'am?

17:56.276 --> 17:58.709
I do not see any
ma'ams around here.

17:58.745 --> 18:00.211
You call me Trish, you hear?

18:00.246 --> 18:01.746
- Yes, ma'am, I mean Trish.

18:01.781 --> 18:05.650
- Hey, and we got a little
something for you, darling.

18:05.685 --> 18:10.021
- A teddy bear, oh my
gosh, mom it's so cute.

18:10.056 --> 18:12.623
- That is Wedding Elvis.

18:12.659 --> 18:14.926
- "Thank you very much."

18:14.961 --> 18:16.194
- Let me get you
guys checked in.

18:16.229 --> 18:17.328
- Okay.

18:17.363 --> 18:18.496
- Major, did I hear
you were stationed

18:18.531 --> 18:19.964
at the base in Jackson?

18:19.999 --> 18:21.899
- I was, retired now.

18:21.935 --> 18:23.935
I'm stationed in Scottsdale.

18:23.970 --> 18:25.770
- Although for
him, retired means

18:25.805 --> 18:29.240
jogging five miles every morning
and remodeling the house.

18:29.275 --> 18:31.943
- So Clay, now that
you're getting married,

18:31.978 --> 18:33.945
what's next for you?

18:33.980 --> 18:37.014
- Yes sir, I have several
big shows coming this summer.

18:37.050 --> 18:38.950
I have--
- I meant long term.

18:38.985 --> 18:40.818
You know, an actual career.

18:40.854 --> 18:43.988
- You all must be so
exhausted from your trip.

18:44.023 --> 18:45.156
Maybe a nap?

18:45.191 --> 18:46.691
- Hey, once we get
settled, we need

18:46.726 --> 18:48.426
to start planning the big day.

18:48.461 --> 18:49.660
How about a get-together
here tomorrow,

18:49.696 --> 18:51.062
we'll kick around some ideas?

18:51.097 --> 18:52.997
- Strategy session,
good idea, Sheppard.

18:53.032 --> 18:54.599
- We have so many
decisions to make.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.334
Is that good for you, Laurel?

18:56.369 --> 18:59.303
- How about my house after
work, I could fix us a bite?

18:59.339 --> 19:01.806
- Oh, don't you worry about
food, I'll whip something up.

19:01.841 --> 19:02.907
- I can bring some finger foods.

19:02.942 --> 19:05.510
- Oh, no need, I already
got the menu all planned.

19:05.545 --> 19:07.044
- But, we just decided.

19:07.080 --> 19:10.114
- Honey, it is a long drive
from Mid-East Tennessee,

19:10.150 --> 19:11.182
I needed something
to pass the time.

19:11.217 --> 19:13.017
Can y'all believe that
we're gonna have a wedding

19:13.052 --> 19:15.186
in two and a half weeks?

19:15.221 --> 19:16.120
Tyler, get a photo.

19:16.156 --> 19:16.888
- Yes, ma'am, here we go.

19:16.990 --> 19:17.989
Everybody in tight.
- Come on in.

19:18.024 --> 19:19.790
Here we go, get everybody.

19:19.826 --> 19:21.726
- One, Major, smile.

19:21.761 --> 19:22.727
Two, three.

19:27.534 --> 19:29.700
- And if you'll sign here.
- Yep.

19:29.736 --> 19:31.469
- And here.
- Mm-hmm.

19:32.305 --> 19:34.205
- One more right here.

19:36.176 --> 19:39.310
- Now, that is a beautiful ring.

19:39.345 --> 19:41.646
And I was wondering when
Clay was going to get around

19:41.681 --> 19:43.814
to finally popping the question.

19:43.850 --> 19:45.183
It is Clay, isn't it?

19:45.218 --> 19:48.686
- Of course, but I promise
it won't impact my work.

19:48.721 --> 19:49.954
- You don't have
to tell me that.

19:49.989 --> 19:52.089
I have the utmost faith in you.

19:52.125 --> 19:54.525
- Thank you, that
means so much to me.

19:54.561 --> 19:57.862
Clay is emailing our Save
The Dates this morning.

19:57.897 --> 19:59.363
June 1st.

19:59.399 --> 20:00.498
- That soon?

20:00.533 --> 20:01.999
- I hope you and
Glenda can make it.

20:02.035 --> 20:04.969
- Well, you just
try to keep us away.

20:05.004 --> 20:07.104
How's the wedding
planning going?

20:07.140 --> 20:09.307
- Well, two servings
of pretty good

20:09.342 --> 20:11.943
with a side order of panic.

20:11.978 --> 20:16.113
- Well, if there's anything I
can do, you just let me know.

20:16.149 --> 20:18.516
- Well, there actually is.

20:19.385 --> 20:22.453
If you could sign right here.
- Okay.

20:22.488 --> 20:24.422
Is that it?
- Yes, sir.

20:26.459 --> 20:29.794
Now this is what I
call perfect timing.

20:29.829 --> 20:31.495
- She said to be
here on the dot.

20:31.531 --> 20:32.363
- Me too.

20:33.933 --> 20:35.900
(sighing) Is that
your momma's cooking?

20:35.935 --> 20:37.401
Smells good.

20:37.437 --> 20:42.106
- Give her a barbecue pit and
a few hours and magic happens.

20:42.141 --> 20:43.874
- Surprise!

20:43.910 --> 20:45.876
- Oh my, what is all this?

20:45.912 --> 20:48.079
- We decided to throw
you a pounding party.

20:48.114 --> 20:49.880
- We expected a
strategy session.

20:49.916 --> 20:53.851
- We did, too, but apparently
Trish had other ideas.

20:53.886 --> 20:55.086
- Are you surprised, mom?

20:55.121 --> 20:56.754
- I sure am.

20:56.789 --> 20:58.089
What's a pounding party?

20:58.124 --> 20:59.690
- Don't tell me you've
been gone so long

20:59.726 --> 21:01.559
you've forgotten all
your Southern traditions.

21:01.594 --> 21:04.595
- I confess, I had no idea
what a pounding party was.

21:04.631 --> 21:07.131
- When a couple gets
married, friends and family

21:07.166 --> 21:09.066
get together and bring
all kinds of things

21:09.102 --> 21:10.568
to outfit the kitchen.

21:10.603 --> 21:11.802
- That's sweet.
- Yep.

21:11.838 --> 21:13.037
- There's more gifts
in the dining room.

21:13.106 --> 21:16.407
- Yeah, just a few necessities
that we saw you were missing.

21:16.442 --> 21:18.743
- In keeping with tradition,

21:18.778 --> 21:21.045
we picked this up
for you as well.

21:21.080 --> 21:23.147
An essential for every kitchen.

21:23.182 --> 21:27.018
- Thank you, Isabelle,
you shouldn't have.

21:29.889 --> 21:31.155
You really shouldn't have.

21:31.190 --> 21:32.690
- It's an avocado slicer.

21:32.725 --> 21:33.791
- Oh.

21:33.826 --> 21:34.925
- I've got one of those,
I call it a knife.

21:34.961 --> 21:37.728
- It's great, it's great,
we love making guacamole.

21:37.764 --> 21:39.130
Thank you.
- Thank you.

21:39.165 --> 21:41.299
- Oh, and Tyler
and I got you this.

21:41.334 --> 21:43.834
We got you a pound of
flour, and a pound of sugar,

21:43.870 --> 21:46.203
and eggs, and milk,
and a pan to mix it in.

21:46.239 --> 21:47.371
- Oh.

21:47.407 --> 21:49.273
- That's why you call
it a pounding party.

21:49.309 --> 21:51.809
- Clever, thank y'all, thanks.

21:53.046 --> 21:56.280
- Oh, and son, since
you're getting married,

21:56.316 --> 21:58.349
you're gonna need this.

21:59.919 --> 22:01.018
- Bourbon?

22:01.054 --> 22:02.520
- It's an old tradition to
bury a bottle at the venue

22:02.555 --> 22:05.089
to ward off any rain
on the wedding day.

22:05.124 --> 22:07.124
- Fascinating, I
did not know that.

22:07.160 --> 22:10.127
- My wife knows just about
every Southern tradition.

22:10.163 --> 22:12.596
Stick around, you
may learn something.

22:12.632 --> 22:13.898
- So who's hungry?

22:13.933 --> 22:16.400
I've got brisket, and
chicken, and ribs.

22:16.436 --> 22:19.203
- Oh it looks delicious,
but I have to pass.

22:19.238 --> 22:20.738
I'm pescatarian.

22:22.275 --> 22:23.474
- Pesca-what?

22:24.143 --> 22:27.278
- The only meat I eat is fish.

22:27.313 --> 22:28.446
- Oh.

22:28.481 --> 22:31.649
- Don't worry about me,
everyone, I'll be fine.

22:31.684 --> 22:34.218
- Well, let me take that
from you, Laurel, honey

22:34.253 --> 22:35.386
- Thanks.

22:36.556 --> 22:38.289
- Laurel, can you come
help me in the kitchen?

22:38.324 --> 22:39.190
- Sure.

22:41.994 --> 22:45.996
Oh, red velvet cupcakes,
would you look at that?

22:46.032 --> 22:47.565
Don't tell me you
made these today.

22:47.600 --> 22:50.801
- Well then I won't, but I did.

22:50.837 --> 22:52.703
These are my son's favorites.

22:52.739 --> 22:55.239
I make a tower like
this for every birthday.

22:55.274 --> 22:57.975
- I thought his favorite
dessert was pecan pie.

22:58.010 --> 23:00.344
- Oh no, red velvet tower.

23:00.380 --> 23:02.380
Clay's heart's delight.

23:03.649 --> 23:06.283
But be careful, it's fragile.

23:07.286 --> 23:11.122
And I'm not talking
about the cupcake, honey.

23:11.157 --> 23:14.759
(curious percussion music)

23:22.067 --> 23:23.801
Major, you wanted the table?

23:23.836 --> 23:26.203
- All right, let's
get down to brass tax.

23:26.239 --> 23:27.471
Now, this wedding
is two weeks away,

23:27.507 --> 23:29.907
so I took the liberty
of creating a schedule.

23:29.942 --> 23:31.642
Everyone knows that
most battles are won

23:31.677 --> 23:33.310
before they're fought.

23:33.346 --> 23:34.512
- It's a military thing.

23:34.547 --> 23:37.615
- Though it's a
wedding, not a war.

23:39.719 --> 23:41.218
- Look at all the colors.

23:41.254 --> 23:43.687
- Well, this is something,
isn't this something, Clay?

23:43.723 --> 23:44.889
- [Clay] It's
something all right.

23:44.924 --> 23:46.791
- What we have
here is a timeline.

23:46.826 --> 23:50.528
It starts on today and runs
through the day of the wedding.

23:50.563 --> 23:54.799
I've broken it down into
days, tasks, and events.

23:56.102 --> 23:57.268
- How festive.

23:57.370 --> 23:59.904
But I always say it's best to
just take one step at a time.

23:59.939 --> 24:02.239
So let's start with
the guest list.

24:02.275 --> 24:05.476
So I have Clay's sisters
and their hubbies and kids.

24:05.511 --> 24:08.078
And the cousins, first,
second, and third.

24:08.114 --> 24:09.513
And our friends and neighbors.

24:09.549 --> 24:11.482
- Mom, you have like
50 people on this list.

24:11.517 --> 24:12.950
- That's just the first page.

24:12.985 --> 24:15.319
- Well I think what
Clay means is that given

24:15.354 --> 24:17.421
the tight schedule,
we think it'd be best

24:17.457 --> 24:19.323
to limit 12 guests each.

24:19.358 --> 24:21.826
- I have to say,
that seems sensible.

24:21.861 --> 24:25.696
- And if I might suggest
a formal wedding.

24:25.731 --> 24:28.466
Men in tuxedos, ladies
in evening gowns.

24:28.501 --> 24:29.733
- Formal?

24:29.769 --> 24:31.101
When Tyler and I got married,

24:31.137 --> 24:34.138
all the ladies wore
big silk flower hats.

24:34.173 --> 24:35.272
It's a party, after all.

24:35.308 --> 24:38.342
- Of course, it is a wedding
not the Kentucky Derby.

24:38.377 --> 24:39.643
- Dad?

24:39.679 --> 24:40.578
- Our neighbor's getting
married at the Kentucky Derby.

24:40.613 --> 24:42.046
- And it was lovely.

24:42.081 --> 24:45.282
Wouldn't be a shame to go
small on such a big day?

24:45.318 --> 24:46.517
Don't you think, Laurel?

24:46.552 --> 24:49.420
- But tradition never
goes out of style,

24:49.455 --> 24:50.855
isn't that right, Laurel?

24:50.890 --> 24:54.658
Maybe the bride should
decide whose idea is better.

24:54.694 --> 24:57.261
- I think the all
the ideas are great.

24:57.296 --> 24:58.796
I can't decide right now.

24:58.831 --> 25:01.365
- Well, honey, you take your
time and give it some thought.

25:01.400 --> 25:03.000
It's your big day, after all.

25:03.035 --> 25:05.236
We don't want to impose
our ideas on you.

25:05.271 --> 25:06.403
- I think one thing
we can all agree on,

25:06.472 --> 25:09.073
is we have a lot to do with
a very short timeframe, so--

25:09.108 --> 25:11.108
- So, back to my chart.
(doorbell ringing)

25:11.143 --> 25:13.811
- She's here, right on time.

25:13.846 --> 25:14.979
- She?

25:15.014 --> 25:16.247
- Major, I don't think
we're gonna need this.

25:16.282 --> 25:18.382
Tyler and I saved the
big news for last.

25:18.417 --> 25:21.452
We got y'all an early
wedding present.

25:21.487 --> 25:22.786
- [Tyler] Tah-dah!

25:22.822 --> 25:24.555
- Hello, everyone.

25:25.458 --> 25:26.357
- Hello.

25:26.392 --> 25:27.925
- You must be Laurel.
- I am.

25:27.960 --> 25:30.060
- Congratulations
to the both of you.

25:30.096 --> 25:31.161
- Thank you.

25:31.197 --> 25:32.663
- I'm Allie Monroe,
and may I say,

25:32.698 --> 25:34.265
it's such a pleasure.

25:34.300 --> 25:37.368
- Allie is one of the
top wedding planners

25:37.403 --> 25:39.303
in all of Tennessee.

25:39.338 --> 25:44.642
- I've brought along photos of
my work for inspiration, yes.

25:45.378 --> 25:46.644
Let's just get this
out of the way.

25:46.679 --> 25:48.779
You can set that there, perfect.

25:48.814 --> 25:51.615
Now, I know we have a
million things to cover,

25:51.651 --> 25:54.151
including seeing the venue.

25:54.186 --> 25:57.021
- Okay, we can call
Kathy on Monday.

25:57.056 --> 25:59.924
- Oh, no need, I've already
made an appointment.

25:59.959 --> 26:02.626
Tomorrow morning, 9 a.m. sharp.

26:04.530 --> 26:06.463
- Okay, sounds good.

26:12.705 --> 26:12.736
- This space is lovely.

26:16.542 --> 26:19.810
What a dream I can
create for you.

26:19.845 --> 26:23.781
I see gold aisle runners with
enormous cymbidium orchids

26:23.816 --> 26:27.818
in mercury-glass vases
wrapped in gold tool.

26:27.853 --> 26:31.188
Votive candles on each
pedestal lining the way.

26:31.223 --> 26:33.023
Are you taking notes?

26:34.193 --> 26:35.926
Ms. Monroe, Allie?

26:37.597 --> 26:41.098
Clay and I were just,
we were thinking.

26:41.801 --> 26:43.567
It's nothing, never mind.

26:43.603 --> 26:47.871
- Honey, we were just
thinking just wildflowers.

26:48.874 --> 26:51.475
- (laughing) "Wildflowers."

26:51.510 --> 26:55.045
You have a sense of humor,
I like that in a client.

26:55.081 --> 26:56.313
- Did Clay say something funny?

26:56.349 --> 27:00.351
- Oh, honey let's just
give Allie a chance.

27:00.386 --> 27:02.052
- Are you sure about this?

27:02.088 --> 27:03.921
- Well, what can I do?

27:03.956 --> 27:07.191
It's a gift from your mom, I
don't want to seem ungrateful.

27:07.226 --> 27:08.292
- I know.

27:08.327 --> 27:09.627
- Let's just hear
what she has in mind.

27:09.662 --> 27:10.928
- Good.

27:10.963 --> 27:15.132
- And here, a canopy of
cherry blossoms with crystals.

27:18.070 --> 27:19.803
- Oh, I love that.

27:21.607 --> 27:24.575
- I'm with you, I'm with you.

27:24.610 --> 27:26.143
- Yay.
- Woo-hoo.

27:28.114 --> 27:33.350
- Okay, that's enough flower
girl practice for now.

27:34.153 --> 27:35.152
How are the invitations
coming along?

27:35.187 --> 27:36.920
- Good, we're almost done.

27:36.956 --> 27:39.189
It would've been
easier to email them.

27:39.225 --> 27:41.492
- And somehow, I don't think
Isabelle would approve.

27:41.527 --> 27:44.028
- Hey mom, can I go over
and play at Lanie's?

27:44.063 --> 27:47.031
- Sure, just leave
the petals outside.

27:47.066 --> 27:47.965
- Okay.
- Okay.

27:48.000 --> 27:49.733
- You know, I think
I'm gonna go monitor

27:49.769 --> 27:50.934
some of that flower power.

27:51.003 --> 27:54.938
- I'll come with you, I've got
wedding programs to design.

27:54.974 --> 27:57.908
- Thank y'all for y'all help.
- See you later.

27:57.943 --> 28:02.212
- Well, no need to send me
an invitation, I'll be there.

28:02.248 --> 28:04.648
In spite of what your
mom seems to think.

28:04.684 --> 28:06.850
One thing's for sure,
if we're all gonna be

28:06.886 --> 28:09.853
one big, happy family
we got a long way to go.

28:09.889 --> 28:11.922
- You are not kidding.

28:11.957 --> 28:13.991
- What if we take
the initiative?

28:14.026 --> 28:15.959
iI host a girls' day out,

28:15.995 --> 28:17.594
and you have a day
out with the guys,

28:17.630 --> 28:21.231
and we can get everybody to
talk and maybe compromise.

28:21.267 --> 28:22.966
- Yeah, maybe we can get one
of them to talk to Allie,

28:23.002 --> 28:25.936
and get her to tone
things down a little.

28:25.971 --> 28:26.837
Or a lot.

28:28.541 --> 28:33.010
Hey, we're gonna get
through this, together.

28:33.045 --> 28:35.512
- You're right, together
we can handle anything,

28:35.548 --> 28:37.214
even our parents.

28:38.217 --> 28:39.616
- What?

28:39.652 --> 28:42.119
- Well, I thought if I said
it out loud, I might buy it.

28:42.154 --> 28:44.221
It didn't work.

28:44.256 --> 28:45.089
- No.

28:51.597 --> 28:55.365
- Oh, a day spa, this is
such a lovely idea, Laurel.

28:55.401 --> 28:58.569
- I agree, it's a
delightful idea.

28:58.604 --> 29:00.938
- You agree, this day
is working out already.

29:00.973 --> 29:04.608
- Well honey, it isn't work
when you're having fun.

29:04.643 --> 29:06.877
- It's so good of you
both to be here for us.

29:06.912 --> 29:10.013
I mean, Clay and I couldn't
do this without y'all.

29:10.049 --> 29:11.348
- We're happy to help.

29:11.383 --> 29:14.518
- Speaking of which, Allie
gave us some homework.

29:14.553 --> 29:18.388
She flagged some cake and design
ideas for us to check out.

29:18.424 --> 29:20.924
- Allie sure has a lot of ideas.

29:20.960 --> 29:21.859
Maybe we can talk about that?

29:21.894 --> 29:23.627
- You know, when Tyler
and I got married,

29:23.662 --> 29:26.830
we had 300 guests, we
had four live music acts,

29:26.866 --> 29:29.733
and folks flew in
from everywhere.

29:29.769 --> 29:30.901
How about you Isabelle?

29:30.970 --> 29:35.105
- Well, the Major and I had
a simple ceremony last year.

29:35.141 --> 29:39.143
Traditional, tasteful,
we didn't want to fuss.

29:39.178 --> 29:42.079
- Is the whole point of a
wedding is to make a fuss?

29:42.114 --> 29:45.716
- Oh, would you look at this
article on wedding cakes.

29:45.751 --> 29:48.185
- Look at that, that
is a five-tiered peach

29:48.220 --> 29:52.089
with Bourbon and
pecan frosting, yum.

29:52.124 --> 29:53.524
You know what'd be cute?

29:53.559 --> 29:54.892
If we had a groom with a guitar

29:54.927 --> 29:57.427
and a bride with a
microphone on top.

29:57.463 --> 29:58.662
- That's an idea.

29:58.697 --> 30:01.064
- Isn't this lovely,
vanilla buttercream.

30:01.100 --> 30:03.100
- Classics never
go out of style.

30:03.135 --> 30:04.768
(phone buzzing)
- Oh it's the hotel.

30:04.804 --> 30:06.336
We're trying to switch rooms.

30:06.372 --> 30:08.272
The guests across the
hall were playing music

30:08.307 --> 30:11.208
until all hours last night.

30:11.243 --> 30:14.611
- I am so sorry,
were we too loud?

30:14.647 --> 30:17.281
- Hello, yes this
is Mrs. Couper.

30:17.316 --> 30:19.283
- You know, I am so
glad you and Clay

30:19.318 --> 30:21.118
found each other again.

30:21.153 --> 30:23.687
- That means so much to me.

30:23.722 --> 30:26.190
- Well you know when
you left for Chicago,

30:26.225 --> 30:27.791
he took it real hard.

30:27.827 --> 30:29.726
He really missed you.

30:29.762 --> 30:33.063
Can you blame him,
you leaving like that?

30:33.098 --> 30:36.133
- Trish, that
won't happen again.

30:36.168 --> 30:40.103
Cross my heart, Clay and
I are together for life.

30:40.139 --> 30:42.739
- That's what a
mother wants to hear.

30:42.775 --> 30:45.542
Which is why you deserve a
wedding you're gonna remember

30:45.578 --> 30:47.044
for a lifetime.

30:47.079 --> 30:49.079
You don't want some
small ceremony that's

30:49.114 --> 30:50.948
over and done in an hour.

30:50.983 --> 30:55.853
You stick with me, girl, we're
gonna do this thing right.

30:55.888 --> 30:58.355
- You think doves are too much?

30:58.390 --> 30:59.256
- Well--

30:59.291 --> 31:02.292
- Me neither, I'll
talk to Allie about it.

31:02.328 --> 31:04.228
I just love that cake.

31:05.130 --> 31:07.798
- Okay boys, Major
and I are dormy,

31:07.833 --> 31:09.132
two up with two to play.

31:09.168 --> 31:10.834
The pressure is on.

31:10.870 --> 31:12.769
You okay, son, this is the
worst I've seen you play

31:12.805 --> 31:13.937
since you were 10.

31:13.973 --> 31:15.239
- Yeah, if I didn't
know any better,

31:15.274 --> 31:16.540
I'd say you were
losing on purpose.

31:16.575 --> 31:18.308
- No, it's not that, it's just

31:18.344 --> 31:20.043
I have a lot on
my mind with work.

31:20.079 --> 31:21.645
We have a lot of shows
coming up, that's good.

31:21.680 --> 31:24.147
We have two concerts in June,
two more on the horizon.

31:24.183 --> 31:26.917
- You know, that horizon's
gonna expand indefinitely

31:26.952 --> 31:27.951
once you get married.

31:27.987 --> 31:32.055
College funds, mortgages,
retirement planning.

31:32.091 --> 31:32.923
- He didn't make the PGA Tour,

31:32.958 --> 31:36.059
but Clay makes a
good living, Major.

31:36.095 --> 31:37.261
- Thank you.

31:37.296 --> 31:40.764
- All right, partner,
we need a good one here.

31:40.799 --> 31:42.866
- So, Ted, what line
of work are you in?

31:42.902 --> 31:45.435
- I'm an electrician,
I own my own business.

31:45.471 --> 31:48.238
- Excellent, an electrician.

31:48.274 --> 31:50.040
Reliable.
- Thank you.

31:50.809 --> 31:53.277
- Something everybody needs.

31:53.312 --> 31:55.379
- Kind of like music,
especially in Memphis.

31:55.414 --> 31:56.813
- Mm-hmm.

31:56.849 --> 31:59.316
- Of course it's always
good to have a backup plan

31:59.351 --> 32:01.251
in case something goes wrong.

32:01.287 --> 32:03.053
- In my experience, if
you have a backup plan,

32:03.088 --> 32:06.023
you end up doing
the backup plan.

32:06.058 --> 32:06.924
- Fore!

32:12.331 --> 32:13.430
- Sorry.

32:14.300 --> 32:15.132
- Great.

32:16.402 --> 32:18.302
- Here, have a backup.

32:22.675 --> 32:25.642
- [Isabelle] This really was
a wonderful idea, thank you.

32:25.678 --> 32:27.811
- Oh, I'm so glad
you enjoyed it.

32:27.846 --> 32:30.213
It sure is nice to get
pampered every now and then.

32:30.249 --> 32:33.350
- Although, I must say it
took me a little bit to relax

32:33.385 --> 32:36.153
listening to all of those
over the top wedding ideas.

32:36.188 --> 32:38.755
- I know, but some of them
aren't so bad, don't you think?

32:38.791 --> 32:42.960
- Well, you know what
they say, "Less is more."

32:42.995 --> 32:45.729
- (hoots) These were right
outside the steam room.

32:45.764 --> 32:48.799
Imagine if we had lost these.

32:48.834 --> 32:50.000
- Imagine.

32:50.035 --> 32:51.935
- Call me, we'll talk.

32:55.174 --> 32:58.508
(gentle guitar music)

32:59.812 --> 33:02.846
(cheerful humming)

33:13.659 --> 33:16.560
- Is this a bank or
the Grand Ole Opry?

33:16.595 --> 33:18.929
- Sometimes I just
can't help myself.

33:18.964 --> 33:21.131
- Thought I could walk you home.

33:21.166 --> 33:22.733
Can I carry your books?

33:22.768 --> 33:23.767
- I accept.

33:26.972 --> 33:29.339
- So, how was the big
morning with the ladies?

33:29.375 --> 33:31.341
- Torn between two mothers.

33:31.377 --> 33:32.576
One wants everything bigger,

33:32.611 --> 33:34.945
the other wants
everything smaller.

33:34.980 --> 33:37.848
You know how spas are
serene and relaxing?

33:37.883 --> 33:38.548
- Yeah.

33:38.584 --> 33:41.151
- Think the opposite of that.

33:41.186 --> 33:44.154
How was golf with the boys?

33:44.189 --> 33:47.024
- Did everything I
could, I even lost.

33:47.059 --> 33:48.525
- You lost at golf?

33:48.560 --> 33:50.861
- Look, it was worth
a shot, but your dad

33:50.896 --> 33:53.030
still seems to think I
produce puppet shows.

33:53.065 --> 33:55.265
- Maybe you're trying too
hard, is that possible?

33:55.300 --> 33:57.434
- Well, he's gonna
be my father-in-law,

33:57.469 --> 34:00.337
so I care about what he thinks.

34:01.740 --> 34:02.939
- He'll come around.

34:02.975 --> 34:04.274
On the bright side,
your mom and I

34:04.309 --> 34:07.477
actually got along
pretty well today.

34:07.513 --> 34:09.279
She had some fun ideas.

34:09.314 --> 34:11.948
- Really? For instance?

34:11.984 --> 34:15.118
- Maybe not fun, fun
but doves at a reception

34:15.154 --> 34:18.388
and something about
a confetti cannon?

34:18.424 --> 34:19.823
- I hope you heard wrong.

34:19.858 --> 34:21.825
- Oh, I forgot to tell
you, Sally said she found

34:21.860 --> 34:23.994
the perfect band to
play at our reception.

34:24.029 --> 34:26.296
She wants us all to go hear
them tonight at Lafayette's.

34:26.331 --> 34:27.597
- So she's doing my job now?

34:27.633 --> 34:29.766
- Let's stop by my
place on the way.

34:29.802 --> 34:32.936
I don't wanna wear
my work clothes.

34:35.908 --> 34:39.242
♪ On my way back to Memphis

34:39.278 --> 34:42.979
♪ To my simple way of life

34:43.015 --> 34:46.316
♪ Back to that booth
at the P and H ♪

34:46.351 --> 34:50.821
♪ Oh how I miss these
Memphis nights ♪

34:52.324 --> 34:54.191
- Sal.
- You made it.

34:56.161 --> 34:57.294
- [Laurel] So, is this the band?

34:57.329 --> 34:58.361
- This is just the warmup.

34:58.397 --> 35:00.997
The other act is on later
and you'll love them.

35:01.033 --> 35:02.299
- What's the name, I
probably know them.

35:02.334 --> 35:05.102
- It's a surprise, relax.

35:05.137 --> 35:06.069
- All right, did our
parents show up yet?

35:06.105 --> 35:09.639
- They did and trying
to have a good time.

35:09.675 --> 35:12.142
Well, two of them at least.

35:13.312 --> 35:15.879
- Let's go say hey
to dad and Isabelle.

35:15.914 --> 35:19.649
- We'll see you soon.
- All right, got it.

35:20.586 --> 35:22.252
- They're here.

35:22.287 --> 35:23.353
- Hey y'all.

35:23.388 --> 35:25.989
