38:59.738 --> 39:01.204
- Do you mind if
we browse a bit?

39:01.239 --> 39:03.540
- Make yourselves at home, I'm
around if you need anything.

39:03.575 --> 39:05.408
- Okay.
- Thank you.

39:06.345 --> 39:08.411
- You two were
terrific last night.

39:08.447 --> 39:10.347
You should take that
act on the road again.

39:10.382 --> 39:12.115
- Right, maybe we'll
squeeze that between

39:12.150 --> 39:13.483
the catering and the flowers.

39:13.518 --> 39:17.620
- Okay, okay point
taken, but you and Clay

39:17.656 --> 39:19.589
do make beautiful
music together.

39:19.624 --> 39:21.191
- Tell that to my father.

39:21.226 --> 39:23.860
What was his excuse for
skipping out last night?

39:23.895 --> 39:26.696
- Well, he told me that he had
to be up early for something.

39:26.732 --> 39:28.832
- His morning run.

39:28.867 --> 39:30.233
The fact is that he's
just not interested

39:30.268 --> 39:31.201
in that side of me.

39:31.236 --> 39:32.902
I mean, you remember,
he only came to what

39:32.938 --> 39:34.404
like two of our shows.

39:34.439 --> 39:38.441
- His loss if you ask me.
- I know, right.

39:38.477 --> 39:39.275
Okay, we've only got an hour

39:39.311 --> 39:42.379
before Trish and
Isabelle get here.

39:42.414 --> 39:44.347
I swear those two.

39:44.383 --> 39:47.350
- Well, this is the perfect
place to take your mind

39:47.386 --> 39:49.486
off of all of that

39:49.521 --> 39:52.522
Welcome to wedding wonderland.

39:52.557 --> 39:55.425
- Oh my gosh, we hit
the jackpot here, Sal.

39:55.460 --> 39:57.227
Oh, what do you think?

39:57.262 --> 39:58.495
- Beautiful.

39:58.530 --> 40:00.463
What did your mom wear
on her wedding day?

40:00.499 --> 40:04.567
- It was all white lace, but
she had her wild side too.

40:04.603 --> 40:07.670
She had her shoes
covered in rhinestones.

40:07.706 --> 40:10.807
- Rhinestones,
now we're talking.

40:12.677 --> 40:14.711
- You're early.
- So are you.

40:14.746 --> 40:16.746
Hold on to your
hat, there's news.

40:16.782 --> 40:18.615
- Yes, there is news.

40:18.650 --> 40:20.216
- Allie has booked
a horse and carriage

40:20.252 --> 40:21.785
to take y'all to the chapel.

40:21.820 --> 40:22.485
- Oh.

40:22.521 --> 40:23.553
- She asked me what I thought.

40:23.588 --> 40:24.954
I just couldn't resist.

40:24.990 --> 40:28.224
- It's true, she couldn't,
she really couldn't.

40:28.260 --> 40:30.393
So, you see anything you like?

40:30.429 --> 40:32.729
- Well, I was thinking that--

40:32.764 --> 40:34.397
- Thank goodness
we're here to help.

40:34.433 --> 40:35.665
All right, now,
let's get to work.

40:35.700 --> 40:36.866
Come on, let's get to work.

40:36.902 --> 40:39.969
(swanky jazz music)

41:08.166 --> 41:10.099
- Which one did you like?

41:10.135 --> 41:11.401
- If it's the one
with the train,

41:11.436 --> 41:12.602
we're gonna have to
plan your entrance.

41:12.671 --> 41:16.272
- Well, y'all are just gonna
have to wait for the big day.

41:16.308 --> 41:17.540
Let's just say it's
the perfect dress,

41:17.576 --> 41:19.609
and I couldn't have
done it without y'all.

41:19.644 --> 41:21.611
- You're welcome.
- You're welcome.

41:21.646 --> 41:24.080
- [Sal] Good answer.

41:24.115 --> 41:26.716
- I know which one.
- Me too.

41:27.552 --> 41:29.686
- Mr. Sheppard, welcome back.
- Thank you.

41:29.721 --> 41:31.721
- I have your rings right here.

41:31.756 --> 41:33.623
Here comes the bride.

41:34.292 --> 41:35.492
- [Clay] Wow, that's perfect.

41:35.527 --> 41:37.961
- And yours, very handsome.

41:41.032 --> 41:41.831
- Huh.

41:43.535 --> 41:45.468
- A wedding band does
reflect its owner,

41:45.504 --> 41:48.404
and I do recall
you're a musician.

41:48.440 --> 41:52.342
- Could we maybe go with
something a tad more?

41:53.345 --> 41:54.477
- Not a problem.

41:54.513 --> 41:57.146
Let me show you some
simple gold bands.

41:57.182 --> 41:59.549
- Thanks.
- Be right back.

41:59.584 --> 42:00.617
- Are you letting
the major get to you?

42:00.652 --> 42:05.221
- No, it's just if I'm
going to be settling down,

42:05.257 --> 42:08.358
perhaps I should settle down.

42:08.393 --> 42:10.660
- Yeah, that sounds
like the Major talking.

42:10.695 --> 42:12.795
- Our venue in New Orleans,
it just lost its permit

42:12.831 --> 42:16.232
so maybe I do need to
start looking for something

42:16.268 --> 42:17.467
a little more stable.

42:17.502 --> 42:18.835
- Really?

42:18.870 --> 42:20.703
What would that be?

42:22.474 --> 42:23.873
- Look, I know you're
right, but these plans,

42:23.909 --> 42:26.075
everything's been
moving so fast.

42:26.111 --> 42:29.445
Was your wedding
this out of control?

42:29.481 --> 42:32.882
- Son, every wedding is
its own kind of crazy.

42:32.918 --> 42:35.852
Dealing with two families,
twice the stress.

42:35.887 --> 42:37.654
But go easy on yourself.

42:37.689 --> 42:39.789
The shower this weekend
will be a blast.

42:39.824 --> 42:43.259
Your mom's got this
great idea for it.

42:46.097 --> 42:48.364
- You know what you need,

42:48.400 --> 42:49.499
a romantic night out.

42:49.601 --> 42:52.835
Just you and Laurel away from
all this wedding madness.

42:52.871 --> 42:57.006
- That's the best idea
I've heard so far.

42:57.042 --> 42:59.542
I'm gonna go with this one.

43:01.713 --> 43:04.080
- No way, a pink Cadillac?

43:05.083 --> 43:07.083
Did you trade your
car in for that?

43:07.118 --> 43:08.851
- For my fiancee,
it's only the best.

43:08.887 --> 43:10.820
- If I didn't know any
better, I would think

43:10.855 --> 43:12.755
you were Prince Charming.

43:12.791 --> 43:13.923
- Who said I wasn't?

43:13.959 --> 43:16.893
Your carriage
awaits, Cinderella.

43:17.862 --> 43:19.729
- So, where are we headed?

43:19.764 --> 43:22.665
- A little trip down memory
lane, and all the wedding talk--

43:22.701 --> 43:24.634
- Is off-limits.
- Exactly.

43:24.669 --> 43:29.372
- All right, your Highness,
let's get this carriage going.

43:29.407 --> 43:31.708
(cheering)

43:31.743 --> 43:35.912
(optimistic orchestral music)

43:44.789 --> 43:46.289
You really are Prince Charming.

43:46.324 --> 43:48.825
- Well this is a
full-service date.

43:48.860 --> 43:50.793
- We really have this
all to ourselves?

43:50.829 --> 43:52.128
- Yes we do.

43:52.163 --> 43:53.830
- Clay, how in world did you?

43:53.865 --> 43:57.133
- I know a guy who
knows a guy, you know.

43:57.168 --> 43:58.735
- You're amazing.

43:58.770 --> 44:01.237
You remember the last
time we were up here?

44:01.272 --> 44:03.172
- I do, senior prom.

44:03.208 --> 44:04.340
- That's right.

44:04.376 --> 44:05.642
- You know, I'm not
sure if I remember

44:05.677 --> 44:06.809
the first song we
slow danced to.

44:06.845 --> 44:10.079
But I do remember Major
having his 10 o'clock curfew.

44:10.115 --> 44:12.448
- Well that's old
news, curfew's 11 now.

44:12.484 --> 44:14.717
- 11, so we don't get
to stay out late enough

44:14.753 --> 44:16.919
to see the pink Cadillac
turn into a pumpkin?

44:16.955 --> 44:17.820
- Nope.

44:20.925 --> 44:22.091
You know it was my
dad who pushed me

44:22.127 --> 44:23.960
to go to business school.

44:23.995 --> 44:26.129
- Backup plan?
- Exactly.

44:26.865 --> 44:29.165
When I got the job
at Chicago Financial,

44:29.200 --> 44:30.700
he was over the moon.

44:30.735 --> 44:32.902
It's like I'm a flower
and he only gives sunlight

44:32.937 --> 44:35.938
in the direction he
wants me to grow.

44:35.974 --> 44:37.306
- I'm sure he means well.

44:37.342 --> 44:39.642
- This coming from the
same guy who's sure

44:39.678 --> 44:41.744
that my dad doesn't like him.

44:41.780 --> 44:43.880
- Look, enough
about the parents.

44:43.915 --> 44:46.349
Tonight is gonna be about us.

44:47.085 --> 44:50.019
(phone dinging)

44:52.023 --> 44:52.922
That was my sister.

44:52.957 --> 44:56.793
She has these questions
about gift registry.

44:56.828 --> 44:59.395
- Allie booked a
celebrity chef who needs

44:59.431 --> 45:01.397
to finalize the
dinner, but our mothers

45:01.433 --> 45:03.066
can't agree on the menu.

45:03.101 --> 45:04.434
(phone dings)

45:04.469 --> 45:08.371
Oh, and Isabelle is complaining
about the dove wranglers.

45:08.406 --> 45:10.006
- Dove wranglers?

45:10.041 --> 45:13.876
- Well, you can't hire the
doves without their people.

45:13.912 --> 45:15.311
(phone dinging)

45:15.346 --> 45:17.413
- Okay, we're gonna
turn these off,

45:17.449 --> 45:18.581
and save it for tomorrow.

45:18.616 --> 45:20.016
- But--
- No, no, no.

45:20.051 --> 45:22.351
No more interruptions.

45:22.387 --> 45:24.287
- Well except for one.

45:27.025 --> 45:30.126
(gentle rock music)

45:36.901 --> 45:38.835
May I have this dance?

45:38.870 --> 45:41.204
- Clay Sheppard,
you did remember.

45:41.239 --> 45:42.405
- How could I forget?

45:42.440 --> 45:45.875
- It's only the best
dance of my life.

45:50.415 --> 45:53.082
- This is just what
we needed, just us.

45:53.118 --> 45:56.185
♪ Falling in love with you

45:56.221 --> 45:59.055
(ducks quacking)

46:01.893 --> 46:06.996
♪ For I can't help

46:07.732 --> 46:11.100
♪ Falling in love with you

46:25.583 --> 46:27.683
- [Trish] Ahoy, you two!

46:28.686 --> 46:29.385
- Hello.

46:29.420 --> 46:30.953
- Sir, Major.

46:30.989 --> 46:32.688
- Where do these go?

46:34.092 --> 46:35.625
- Permission to come aboard.

46:35.660 --> 46:37.894
- Permission granted.

46:37.929 --> 46:40.763
Everybody, this is
Mr. Franklin, my boss,

46:40.799 --> 46:42.198
and his sweet wife, Miss Glenda.

46:42.233 --> 46:43.432
- Hello.

46:43.468 --> 46:45.001
- I see you've got a band.

46:45.036 --> 46:48.070
Now, you save me a
dance, young lady, okay?

46:48.106 --> 46:51.207
(jaunty brass music)

47:09.127 --> 47:11.494
(cheering)

47:14.833 --> 47:17.700
- Oh, Vivian, this is adorable.

47:18.870 --> 47:21.838
(everyone swooning)

47:21.873 --> 47:24.140
- We're ready for the cake pull?

47:24.175 --> 47:25.241
- Cake what?

47:25.276 --> 47:26.843
- Oh, it's a game
that tells the future

47:26.878 --> 47:28.377
of the girls in
the wedding party.

47:28.413 --> 47:32.215
- All right, girls,
everybody pick a ribbon.

47:33.051 --> 47:34.984
One, two, three, pull.

47:38.056 --> 47:39.088
- It's an arrow.

47:39.123 --> 47:41.924
- Look at that, that means
you're full of wisdom.

47:41.960 --> 47:43.292
- And I've got a
four-leaf clover.

47:43.328 --> 47:45.061
- That means that
you've got a bunch

47:45.096 --> 47:48.264
of good luck coming your way.

47:48.299 --> 47:50.700
What'd you get, honey?

47:50.735 --> 47:51.868
- [Clay] Does the bride
get her lucky charm?

47:51.936 --> 47:54.637
- Just the girls, the bride
already has her lucky charm.

47:54.672 --> 47:56.005
- Yes, you do.

47:56.941 --> 47:58.040
- I do.

48:00.044 --> 48:00.710
- You are gonna be saying that

48:00.745 --> 48:03.279
pretty soon for real, you know?

48:03.314 --> 48:05.648
- How do you think
it's all going?

48:05.683 --> 48:06.883
- Better now.

48:07.752 --> 48:08.618
I think your dad
thought that the boat

48:08.686 --> 48:11.520
was gonna go down
with all these people.

48:11.556 --> 48:14.090
- Well, your folks do
have a lot of friends.

48:14.125 --> 48:15.424
- [Clay] I know.

48:15.460 --> 48:19.061
- Wow, that view, never
gets old, does it?

48:20.365 --> 48:24.400
And, you mind if I steal
her away for a dance?

48:24.435 --> 48:25.568
- Be my guest.

48:25.603 --> 48:28.804
- I've danced with
everybody else.

48:28.840 --> 48:31.440
Don't step on my toes,
I won't step on yours.

48:31.476 --> 48:34.043
- I can't promise that.
- Okay.

48:44.589 --> 48:45.888
- Major.
- Hey.

48:47.125 --> 48:48.124
- Where's Isabelle?

48:48.159 --> 48:50.393
- Below, lying down.

48:50.428 --> 48:51.994
Not too good on the water.

48:52.030 --> 48:53.095
- Ah.

48:53.831 --> 48:56.699
- Wow, you know, when
your parents said

48:56.734 --> 48:59.969
they were bringing family,
I didn't realize it meant

49:00.004 --> 49:02.471
all of East Tennessee.

49:02.507 --> 49:04.140
- I know my folks
have their own style,

49:04.175 --> 49:05.841
but it comes from a
good place, I promise.

49:05.877 --> 49:09.278
They take things a
bit too far sometimes.

49:09.314 --> 49:10.413
- You think?

49:13.718 --> 49:15.184
- You know, maybe
I can fix this.

49:15.219 --> 49:16.986
- Now, you can't
un-invite guests, son,

49:17.021 --> 49:18.554
I wouldn't ask them to.

49:18.589 --> 49:21.657
- It's not what I
meant, excuse me.

49:24.262 --> 49:26.162
- Okay, okay, perfect.

49:29.567 --> 49:30.800
Bye-bye, now.

49:31.836 --> 49:33.402
Guess who just spoke
to three harpist

49:33.438 --> 49:35.071
to play the wedding march?

49:35.106 --> 49:35.972
- Wow.

49:36.040 --> 49:38.708
I was thinking maybe
just a good guitar.

49:38.743 --> 49:39.709
- Oh, Clay.

49:41.012 --> 49:42.678
- Can we talk for one second?

49:42.714 --> 49:43.813
- Sure.

49:43.848 --> 49:46.916
- Laurel and I were
discussing maybe,

49:46.951 --> 49:50.920
maybe what we need is
just a little bit less.

49:50.955 --> 49:52.321
- I don't follow.

49:54.726 --> 49:56.559
- We appreciate everything
that you've been doing

49:56.594 --> 49:57.994
for this wedding,
it's been great.

49:58.029 --> 50:01.630
But it's becoming just
a little too much.

50:01.666 --> 50:02.965
- Too much?

50:03.001 --> 50:05.735
Those words aren't in my
vocabulary, what do you mean?

50:05.770 --> 50:07.970
- The harps, and the doves,
and confetti cannons,

50:08.006 --> 50:10.139
and horse-drawn carriages.

50:11.409 --> 50:15.111
Maybe if we could just scale
things back just a little.

50:15.146 --> 50:17.880
- Change my plans,
all of my plans

50:17.915 --> 50:19.482
with five days left, huh?

50:19.517 --> 50:21.784
When I have been
working night and day

50:21.819 --> 50:24.920
to make all of this
happen for you.

50:27.492 --> 50:28.891
I don't do simple.

50:28.926 --> 50:33.696
If you wanted simple, why did
you get a wedding planner?

50:34.966 --> 50:37.099
- Well if you remember, it
wasn't our idea to start with.

50:37.135 --> 50:39.835
- How's it going, you two?

50:39.871 --> 50:42.138
- I'll tell you how it's going.

50:42.173 --> 50:43.005
I quit.

50:44.208 --> 50:45.207
- Allie, Clay?

50:47.745 --> 50:48.844
What happened?

50:48.880 --> 50:51.313
- I may have said
something to upset her.

50:51.349 --> 50:52.815
- She just quit.

50:52.850 --> 50:55.584
- Yeah, I know, that's not good.

51:00.224 --> 51:01.357
Thank you.

51:05.830 --> 51:08.798
Allie just took all the
vendors and contacts with her.

51:08.833 --> 51:10.499
- (sighing) Great.

51:10.535 --> 51:15.704
So we're back to square one
with five days for the wedding.

51:16.641 --> 51:19.341
We're gonna need
a florist, a DJ.

51:19.377 --> 51:22.044
Caterer, tables,
chairs, decorations.

51:22.080 --> 51:25.081
We don't even have a minister
to perform the ceremony.

51:25.116 --> 51:26.148
- No need to panic yet.

51:26.184 --> 51:29.485
I'm gonna figure this
out, I'm a problem-solver.

51:29.520 --> 51:32.788
- I don't know, I think
maybe Isabelle was right,

51:32.824 --> 51:34.223
"Less is more."

51:39.163 --> 51:42.198
- Laurel, you're gonna
get the wedding you want

51:42.233 --> 51:43.766
one way or another.

51:45.002 --> 51:46.802
- [Laurel] So you're actually
gonna make this happen?

51:46.838 --> 51:50.239
- No, we are gonna make
this happen as a team.

51:50.274 --> 51:52.641
- Well then, we
better stop talking

51:52.677 --> 51:55.077
and start getting things done.

51:55.113 --> 51:58.714
♪ A little bit conversation
a little more action please ♪

51:58.749 --> 52:03.018
♪ All this time for bringing
satisfaction in me ♪

52:03.054 --> 52:05.121
♪ A little more light
a little more fluff ♪

52:05.156 --> 52:07.056
♪ A little less kind
a little more spunk ♪

52:07.091 --> 52:08.491
♪ Just to let you know
we left you behind baby ♪

52:08.526 --> 52:09.959
♪ Baby make it funny

52:09.994 --> 52:11.060
♪ Spunky spunky

52:11.095 --> 52:12.461
♪ Make it funny (funky funky)

52:12.497 --> 52:15.498
(upbeat pop music)

52:31.816 --> 52:34.183
(ritzy piano music)

52:34.218 --> 52:35.885
- It's kind of has that.

52:35.920 --> 52:37.720
- [Isabelle] Where are
you gonna put that?

52:37.755 --> 52:38.854
- Into the pews.
- Oh.

52:38.890 --> 52:41.757
- [Trish] I think we can
put these on the ends of it.

52:41.792 --> 52:43.826
- Hey, is everything
under control?

52:43.861 --> 52:45.227
- Tiny bit crazy.
- Yeah?

52:45.263 --> 52:47.229
- But we were making
some progress.

52:47.265 --> 52:49.398
Sally said that her friend,
at the design studio

52:49.433 --> 52:52.268
can do the photography
work at the wedding,

52:52.303 --> 52:53.836
so that's covered.
- Good.

52:53.871 --> 52:55.004
- Anything on your end?

52:55.039 --> 52:56.572
- Yeah, remember Jim, my roadie?

52:56.607 --> 52:57.773
He wanted to be the chef?

52:57.808 --> 52:59.875
He's now running
Delta's Kitchen so he's

52:59.911 --> 53:01.143
got the catering covered.

53:01.179 --> 53:02.511
- Oh, good.

53:02.547 --> 53:05.147
- But, we're still
missing a minister.

53:05.183 --> 53:07.116
- Maybe we can call
Reverend Olson.

53:07.151 --> 53:09.351
He was my mom's
pastor growing up,

53:09.387 --> 53:11.887
and they really close.
- Okay.

53:11.923 --> 53:13.155
- He lives in Little Rock now,

53:13.191 --> 53:14.790
so I'll give him a call
and see if he can do it.

53:14.825 --> 53:16.258
- Good idea.
- I think so too.

53:16.294 --> 53:19.361
- Hey mom, do the
horseshoes go up or down?

53:19.397 --> 53:21.297
- Definitely up,
you don't want all

53:21.332 --> 53:24.500
that good light to pour out.

53:24.535 --> 53:26.535
We need all we can get.

53:28.973 --> 53:32.141
- Hey, how can I be
more useful to you?

53:32.176 --> 53:35.411
- I promised Emma ice
cream over an hour ago.

53:35.446 --> 53:37.112
Could you?
- Ice cream?

53:37.148 --> 53:39.381
Yeah, that'll be the easiest
thing I've done all day.

53:39.417 --> 53:42.284
Emma, what do you say,
you and me ice cream date?

53:42.320 --> 53:43.786
- Yeah.
- Let's do it.

53:43.821 --> 53:47.022
Hey, it's gonna be okay.
- Thank you.

53:49.193 --> 53:53.229
- Laurel, honey, I think
horseshoes with ribbons

53:53.264 --> 53:56.599
at the end of each pew would
just be lovely, don't you?

53:56.634 --> 53:59.501
- I think roses in
clear, crystal vases

53:59.537 --> 54:01.303
would be a better choice.

54:01.339 --> 54:02.805
- [Trish and Isabelle]
What do you think?

54:02.840 --> 54:06.141
- Well, I do love the
fun of the horseshoes.

54:06.177 --> 54:09.645
And the simple
vases are nice too.

54:09.680 --> 54:13.349
- I think what Laurel is saying
is she wants traditional.

54:13.384 --> 54:14.817
- And I think
what's she's saying

54:14.852 --> 54:17.586
is that she thinks
horseshoes are more fun.

54:17.622 --> 54:18.654
(phone buzzing)

54:18.689 --> 54:20.322
- Oh, I think what
Laurel is saying is that

54:20.358 --> 54:22.925
she needs to take this call.

54:24.362 --> 54:26.161
- This is better.
- This is better.

54:26.197 --> 54:28.464
- This is.
- This is better.

54:29.433 --> 54:31.166
- This is so good.

54:32.336 --> 54:34.270
- It's because you have
all the key ingredients

54:34.305 --> 54:36.272
to a perfect sundae.

54:36.307 --> 54:39.341
You have the chocolate
sauce, the whipped cream,

54:39.377 --> 54:41.110
and the cherry.

54:41.145 --> 54:44.647
- And a really big spoon.
- Exactly.

54:44.682 --> 54:46.415
- Can this be a tradition?

54:46.450 --> 54:47.716
Mom said that when
we're a family,

54:47.752 --> 54:50.653
we gotta pick our own
family traditions.

54:50.688 --> 54:51.987
I pick this one.

54:52.023 --> 54:53.255
- What else?

54:53.291 --> 54:57.159
Let's see, we could
do Monday movie night.

54:58.829 --> 55:02.598
Taco Tuesday, no,
Trampoline Tuesdays.

55:02.633 --> 55:05.534
- All of those, I can't wait.

55:05.569 --> 55:08.504
You know what, me either.

55:08.539 --> 55:09.638
Cheers.

55:10.641 --> 55:11.674
Something on your nose.

55:11.709 --> 55:15.511
(groans)
(Clay laughing)

55:17.315 --> 55:19.481
- Thank you so much.

55:19.517 --> 55:22.518
Good news, Reverend Olson's
flying in for the wedding.

55:22.553 --> 55:23.352
- Really?

55:23.387 --> 55:24.520
- Yep.
- All right.

55:24.555 --> 55:26.055
Almost the last
piece of the puzzle.

55:26.090 --> 55:30.326
- I guess, (sighs) I just wish
everyone were getting along.

55:30.361 --> 55:31.460
- Yeah, thanks Eileen.

55:31.495 --> 55:32.961
- [Eileen] Thank you.

55:32.997 --> 55:36.465
- I had this image of a big
house, one big happy family,

55:36.500 --> 55:37.900
all together for the holidays.

55:37.935 --> 55:39.034
And now it just
seems like a life

55:39.070 --> 55:41.370
of airports and separate visits.

55:41.405 --> 55:42.471
- Yeah.

55:42.506 --> 55:46.642
- I wish your parents would
reach out to my folks.

55:46.677 --> 55:49.878
- Yeah, your parents should
try a little harder, too.

55:49.914 --> 55:51.080
It takes two to tango.

55:51.115 --> 55:53.282
Well in this case, four.

55:53.317 --> 55:55.084
- I know this is
gonna sound crazy,

55:55.119 --> 55:58.554
but I kind of wish
Allie were still here.

55:58.589 --> 55:59.822
- What?
- What in the world

55:59.857 --> 56:01.156
did you say to scare
her off like that?

56:01.192 --> 56:02.291
- Me?

56:02.360 --> 56:03.992
I didn't say anything, she
was a bull in a china shop.

56:04.028 --> 56:07.830
You should be thanking me,
she was driving you nuts.

56:07.865 --> 56:10.666
- Wow.
- You know what I mean.

56:11.635 --> 56:13.068
I just want you to be happy.

56:13.104 --> 56:15.604
- Oh, I'll be happy as soon
as I walk down the aisle

56:15.639 --> 56:17.706
and everyone goes home.

56:18.943 --> 56:22.945
- So I see you've met Tucker,
he's one of our rescue horses.

56:22.980 --> 56:24.613
- He's beautiful.

56:26.884 --> 56:28.317
- Ms. Presley?

56:28.352 --> 56:30.119
- You can call me Priscilla.

56:30.154 --> 56:32.688
So, are you enjoying your
visit here at Graceland?

56:32.723 --> 56:34.223
- Absolutely, it's beautiful.

56:34.258 --> 56:36.392
We're actually getting
married in the chapel.

56:36.427 --> 56:38.394
- Yeah, (stammering)
two days, two days?

56:38.429 --> 56:39.762
- Well, that's the plan, anyway.

56:39.797 --> 56:41.897
- That's so exciting,
congratulations.

56:41.932 --> 56:43.465
- Yeah, Clay.

56:43.501 --> 56:44.233
This is my fiancee, Laurel.

56:44.268 --> 56:45.901
- Laurel.
- Nice meeting you both.

56:45.936 --> 56:46.802
Two days?

56:47.805 --> 56:48.637
- Wow.

56:49.640 --> 56:51.673
- We were excited
when we got engaged,

56:51.709 --> 56:53.642
but it's just been.

56:53.677 --> 56:57.713
- Yeah, it's been hectic
with all the planning

56:57.748 --> 56:59.481
and the details, and.

56:59.517 --> 57:01.183
- I can totally relate.

57:01.218 --> 57:02.351
- Yeah.

57:02.386 --> 57:03.318
- You know, if you
have some time,

57:03.354 --> 57:05.354
I have something that I
would love to show you

57:05.389 --> 57:07.022
that's very special to me.

57:07.057 --> 57:08.123
Are you game?
- Yes.

57:08.159 --> 57:09.625
- Okay.
- Absolutely.

57:09.660 --> 57:11.660
Oh my goodness.
- Let's do it.

57:11.695 --> 57:15.164
(peaceful piano music)

57:16.901 --> 57:19.268
Weddings can be a
whirlwind, that's for sure.

57:19.303 --> 57:21.904
When Elvis and I got
married in Vegas,

57:21.939 --> 57:24.540
we had to sneak out of
this house in Palm Springs

57:24.575 --> 57:27.743
with all our friends to get
away from the paparazzi.

57:27.778 --> 57:29.411
- Oh my gosh, I
can't even imagine.

57:29.447 --> 57:32.181
- Yeah, it was crazy times.

57:32.216 --> 57:35.818
But we had a wedding that
was private, and intimate,

57:35.853 --> 57:38.787
and you know, that's
exactly how we wanted it.

57:38.823 --> 57:40.322
- Right, you know.

57:40.357 --> 57:41.390
- So.

57:41.492 --> 57:44.460
- Sounds like what we
should've had from the start.

57:44.495 --> 57:47.796
- Oh my, your dress
was so beautiful.

57:49.467 --> 57:50.666
- [Priscilla] Thank you.

57:50.701 --> 57:52.434
- [Clay] That was
some tux Elvis had.

57:52.470 --> 57:53.902
- Mm-hmm.

57:53.938 --> 57:55.771
It feels like just yesterday.

57:55.806 --> 57:57.473
- Do you mind me
asking what the two

57:57.508 --> 57:59.141
of you picked as your song.

57:59.176 --> 58:01.643
- "Love Me Tender" of course.

58:02.680 --> 58:04.947
- Naturally, it's
the perfect song.

58:04.982 --> 58:06.081
- Yeah.

58:06.116 --> 58:07.483
- We're hoping to make
it to that first dance.

58:07.518 --> 58:09.051
We still have so much
to pull together,

58:09.086 --> 58:12.521
and our families disagree
about everything.

58:12.556 --> 58:13.989
- Pretty much.

58:14.024 --> 58:16.592
- Well, whatever happens,
the most important thing

58:16.627 --> 58:21.330
is to remember the most
important thing, each other.

58:22.666 --> 58:25.300
Listen, the two of you
seem like a great couple.

58:25.336 --> 58:29.004
I wish you all the happiness
in the world, I truly do.

58:29.039 --> 58:32.574
- Thank you so much,
Priscilla Presley.

58:33.677 --> 58:34.343
- Nice meeting you both.

58:34.378 --> 58:35.744
- Nice meeting you, thank you.

58:35.779 --> 58:37.212
- Good luck, I'm go
gonna take a ride now.

58:37.248 --> 58:38.981
Take care.
- Bye-bye.

58:40.484 --> 58:41.950
Oh my gosh, how embarrassing.

58:41.986 --> 58:43.385
- You called her
Priscilla Presley.

58:43.420 --> 58:44.319
- I know.

58:46.557 --> 58:47.356
Really?

58:49.393 --> 58:52.694
- And that starts
by not compromising.

58:53.664 --> 58:56.265
- Well with our parents,
that's easier said than done.

58:56.300 --> 58:57.499
- Well, we have to try.

58:57.535 --> 59:01.737
And that starts first
thing in the morning.

59:01.772 --> 59:04.540
(majestic music)

59:08.679 --> 59:09.545
- Clay?

59:11.749 --> 59:12.948
You're up early.

59:12.983 --> 59:15.117
- Isabelle said I
might find you here.

59:15.152 --> 59:16.251
- What's up?

59:17.321 --> 59:19.121
- I think we should have a talk.

59:19.156 --> 59:20.122
Man to man.

59:21.692 --> 59:23.759
- Probably overdue.

59:23.794 --> 59:25.494
Walk with me.

59:25.529 --> 59:26.528
- Sir, I can't help
but get the feeling

59:26.564 --> 59:28.797
you have some reservations
with Laurel and me.

59:28.832 --> 59:32.234
- Oh, I don't have any
reservations about Laurel.

59:32.269 --> 59:33.468
- So it's me?

59:34.705 --> 59:37.906
- Clay, I'm sure you're
a fine young man.

59:37.942 --> 59:40.742
It's the music
business I don't trust.

59:40.778 --> 59:42.511
I thought Laurel
had escaped all that

59:42.546 --> 59:44.313
when she got into finance.

59:44.348 --> 59:46.181
- And then I came
back into the picture.

59:46.216 --> 59:48.984
- Brought the music with you.

59:49.019 --> 59:52.854
- Sir, music's a huge part of
my life and Laurel's as well.

59:52.890 --> 59:54.790
There's no getting around that.

59:54.825 --> 59:58.794
- Look, you're going to be
raising my granddaughter,

59:58.829 --> 1:00:00.762
I need to know that
Laurel and Emma

1:00:00.798 --> 1:00:02.731
have somebody that
they can depend on.

1:00:02.766 --> 1:00:05.567
Someone reliable, solid.

1:00:05.603 --> 1:00:06.835
- Yes, sir.

1:00:06.870 --> 1:00:09.371
I get it and you're right.

1:00:09.406 --> 1:00:13.642
My business can be very
unpredictable like life.

1:00:14.645 --> 1:00:16.878
And I'm not sure how I
can put your mind at ease,

1:00:16.914 --> 1:00:19.181
but I'm really
good at what I do.

1:00:19.216 --> 1:00:22.517
And one thing that's never,
never going to change

1:00:22.553 --> 1:00:26.455
is my love for your
daughter, and Emma too.

1:00:26.490 --> 1:00:29.558
And no matter what life
has in store for us,

1:00:29.593 --> 1:00:32.761
we're gonna get
through it together.

1:00:34.264 --> 1:00:38.166
- Laurel said you were
as stubborn as I am.

1:00:38.202 --> 1:00:40.836
Appreciate the straight talk.

1:00:41.872 --> 1:00:44.773
- Wait, sir, is this a
agree to disagree moment?

1:00:44.808 --> 1:00:46.942
- Maybe so, gotta run.

1:00:52.316 --> 1:00:55.350
(soft jazzy music)

1:00:56.720 --> 1:00:58.286
- This can't be right.

1:00:58.322 --> 1:00:59.888
There's only supposed
to be one cake.

1:00:59.923 --> 1:01:01.156
- That's right.

1:01:01.191 --> 1:01:02.624
- Wait, so you're
making two cakes

1:01:02.660 --> 1:01:04.493
for the Couper-Sheppard wedding?

1:01:04.528 --> 1:01:07.562
- One Couper, one Sheppard.

1:01:07.598 --> 1:01:09.197
- Unbelievable.

1:01:09.233 --> 1:01:12.200
- Well, if you only need
one, which one do you want?

1:01:12.236 --> 1:01:13.802
- I'm gonna have to get
back to you on that.

1:01:13.837 --> 1:01:16.071
First, I have two
mothers to talk to.

1:01:16.106 --> 1:01:19.307
(phone buzzing)

1:01:19.343 --> 1:01:21.243
Hello, Reverend Olson?

1:01:23.614 --> 1:01:25.781
I'm so sorry to hear that.

1:01:25.816 --> 1:01:29.885
No, no, no it's okay,
you can just get well.

1:01:30.721 --> 1:01:33.188
Okay. (sighs)

1:01:43.534 --> 1:01:45.267
- We told them 1300 hours.

1:01:45.302 --> 1:01:48.270
- Not everyone runs on
military time, Major.

1:01:48.305 --> 1:01:49.438
They'll be here.

1:01:49.540 --> 1:01:53.875
- Well, there are still a few
things we need to finalize.

1:01:53.911 --> 1:01:55.610
- I've got everything covered.

1:01:55.646 --> 1:01:57.746
But you're welcome to
help if you'd like.

1:01:57.781 --> 1:01:59.414
- Can you imagine
if they were trying

1:01:59.450 --> 1:02:01.149
to do this on their own?

1:02:01.185 --> 1:02:03.318
- I need a trip to the ladies'.

1:02:03.353 --> 1:02:05.320
If the waiter comes
by, order me a salad?

1:02:05.355 --> 1:02:09.357
- Oh, hold up, girl,
I'm gonna go with you.

1:02:16.834 --> 1:02:19.101
- Okay, just lost the
minister to the flu.

1:02:19.136 --> 1:02:22.237
- He was so sorry, but
he sounded sick as a dog.

1:02:22.272 --> 1:02:24.473
- It's okay, we'll get
somebody else, it'll be fine.

1:02:24.508 --> 1:02:26.274
- By tomorrow?

1:02:26.310 --> 1:02:29.077
Forget that the caterer
didn't get the final menu,

1:02:29.113 --> 1:02:31.179
or rather he got
two final menus.

1:02:31.215 --> 1:02:33.715
- Why would he have two final.

1:02:33.751 --> 1:02:35.550
Let me guess, my
mom and Isabelle?

1:02:35.586 --> 1:02:37.219
- I thought you were
handling this, Clay?

1:02:37.254 --> 1:02:39.454
- Laurel, I've been
juggling everything else.

1:02:39.490 --> 1:02:40.555
I can't be everywhere.

1:02:40.591 --> 1:02:42.257
- Well, I can't either.

1:02:42.292 --> 1:02:44.726
Playing referee on every detail,

1:02:44.762 --> 1:02:47.496
the decorations, the
music, the food, the cakes.

1:02:47.531 --> 1:02:49.498
Did I mention we have two cakes?

1:02:49.533 --> 1:02:50.599
- Two?

1:02:50.701 --> 1:02:52.934
- Yeah, one's perfect if we
were in the royal family.

1:02:52.970 --> 1:02:54.536
The other if we
were getting married

1:02:54.571 --> 1:02:56.471
at the Grand Ole Opry.

1:02:56.507 --> 1:02:57.305
- Okay.

1:02:57.341 --> 1:02:58.607
- (sighing) It's
all falling apart.

1:02:58.642 --> 1:03:00.509
Our folks aren't getting along.

1:03:00.544 --> 1:03:02.210
Nobody's on the same page.

1:03:02.246 --> 1:03:04.379
- Let's just, let's
get through tomorrow.

1:03:04.414 --> 1:03:06.782
- I don't wanna
just get through it.

1:03:06.817 --> 1:03:08.683
I want to enjoy it.

1:03:08.719 --> 1:03:11.453
- I know, I know, I know, okay.

1:03:11.488 --> 1:03:13.588
I'm gonna skip lunch,
make a few phone calls.

1:03:13.624 --> 1:03:15.056
- What's the point?

1:03:15.092 --> 1:03:18.426
With no minister,
there's no wedding.

1:03:18.462 --> 1:03:23.598
I don't know, maybe I am just
at the end of my rope, or,

1:03:25.602 --> 1:03:26.701
maybe this is a sign.

1:03:26.737 --> 1:03:30.672
- Sweetie, I promise you
everything is going to be fine.

1:03:30.707 --> 1:03:32.641
Okay, I'll take care of it.

1:03:32.676 --> 1:03:35.443
- I'm sorry, Clay, I
can't do this right now.

1:03:35.479 --> 1:03:38.246
Please apologize for me.

1:03:38.282 --> 1:03:39.147
- Laurel.

1:03:41.385 --> 1:03:44.019
Laurel (sighing).

1:03:44.054 --> 1:03:47.756
(curious woodwind music)

1:03:51.428 --> 1:03:54.095
- Are you sure that's
what they said?

1:03:54.131 --> 1:03:54.830
- Uh-huh.

1:03:54.865 --> 1:03:56.031
- A hundred percent.

1:03:56.066 --> 1:03:58.466
- It's a shame its
gotten to this point.

1:03:58.502 --> 1:04:01.503
- It didn't happen on its own.

1:04:01.538 --> 1:04:04.406
I don't think any of
us helped matters.

1:04:04.441 --> 1:04:07.442
- Now that, we can all agree on.

1:04:07.477 --> 1:04:11.513
- Isabelle, I'm sorry if I
steamrolled you a little bit.

1:04:11.548 --> 1:04:13.748
- And I'm sorry if
I steamrolled you.

1:04:13.784 --> 1:04:17.786
- I think it's cute you
thought you might have.

1:04:17.821 --> 1:04:20.422
- I feel awful about all this.

1:04:20.457 --> 1:04:21.523
- Me too.

1:04:21.558 --> 1:04:23.558
- Well, we made this mess,

1:04:23.594 --> 1:04:27.629
now what are we gonna
do to straighten it out?

1:04:31.268 --> 1:04:33.134
- Mr. Franklin.
- Hello, Clay.

1:04:33.170 --> 1:04:34.970
How are you?
- Good, how are you?

1:04:35.005 --> 1:04:36.671
- Oh, I'm doing well, now if
you're looking for Laurel,

1:04:36.707 --> 1:04:38.039
she's gone for the day.

1:04:38.075 --> 1:04:40.175
- No sir, actually I was
hoping to talk to you.

1:04:40.210 --> 1:04:41.076
Do you have a moment?

1:04:41.111 --> 1:04:43.178
- Well for you, always.

1:04:44.147 --> 1:04:45.513
So what's on your mind?

1:04:45.549 --> 1:04:47.816
- Well, I need some advice.

1:04:48.719 --> 1:04:50.518
- Oh well, I'll try.

1:04:50.554 --> 1:04:53.488
- You and Glenda have had
this wonderful marriage.

1:04:53.523 --> 1:04:55.390
And Laurel and I.

1:04:55.425 --> 1:04:56.625
The truth is, I don't
know where we stand

1:04:56.660 --> 1:04:58.593
with this wedding right now.

1:04:58.629 --> 1:04:59.594
I mean, we've been
bending over backwards

1:04:59.630 --> 1:05:02.497
to please her parents,
to please my parents.

1:05:02.532 --> 1:05:05.667
- And now, you and Laurel
are, you're feeling torn?

1:05:05.702 --> 1:05:06.902
Right?
- Yes.

1:05:06.970 --> 1:05:10.672
Her dad, Isabelle, my parents,
everyone has a different idea

1:05:10.707 --> 1:05:12.207
about what this
wedding should be.

1:05:12.242 --> 1:05:13.408
- Well, I'm sure.

1:05:13.443 --> 1:05:16.411
Like they say, you don't
marry just the person,

1:05:16.446 --> 1:05:17.545
you marry their whole family.

1:05:17.581 --> 1:05:20.515
- And I love her family, I
want them to be happy too.

1:05:20.550 --> 1:05:21.683
- Well of course,
you're a good man,

1:05:21.752 --> 1:05:24.552
and I've known that since the
first moment I've met you.

1:05:24.588 --> 1:05:27.822
But, that doesn't solve
everything, does it?

1:05:27.858 --> 1:05:28.723
- No.

1:05:29.960 --> 1:05:33.128
- You know, I've got this
theory about weddings.

1:05:33.163 --> 1:05:35.797
That weddings are a test
that couples have to pass.

1:05:35.832 --> 1:05:38.400
All that planning,
and stress, and strain

1:05:38.435 --> 1:05:41.336
it pushes couples to see
if they're really ready.

1:05:41.371 --> 1:05:43.538
- I thought we were,
I think we are.

1:05:43.573 --> 1:05:45.540
- But love is complicated.

1:05:45.575 --> 1:05:48.777
I understand that some people
even write songs about it.

1:05:48.812 --> 1:05:52.047
But it boils down to this,
it doesn't really matter

1:05:52.082 --> 1:05:55.517
what anybody else thinKs or
what everybody else things,

1:05:55.552 --> 1:05:58.353
because it's your
day and Laurel's day,

1:05:58.388 --> 1:06:01.022
so make it what you
and Laurel want.

1:06:01.058 --> 1:06:02.390
Because when all
is said and done,

1:06:02.426 --> 1:06:04.259
and everybody else goes home,

1:06:04.294 --> 1:06:07.429
it's just you and
Laurel, and Emma.

1:06:08.632 --> 1:06:10.865
- That's really good
advice for a banker.

1:06:10.901 --> 1:06:13.601
- I haven't always been
a banker, you know.

1:06:13.637 --> 1:06:14.736
You know, actually
back in the day,

1:06:14.771 --> 1:06:16.938
I was a chaplain in the army.

1:06:16.974 --> 1:06:18.340
- Is that so?

1:06:18.375 --> 1:06:20.875
- So trust me, I have heard
it and I've seen it all.

1:06:20.911 --> 1:06:22.744
But let me ask you one question,

1:06:22.779 --> 1:06:25.313
are you crazy about Laurel?

1:06:25.349 --> 1:06:26.648
- Yes.

1:06:26.683 --> 1:06:30.552
- Well good, because I
know she's crazy about you,

1:06:30.587 --> 1:06:32.554
and as long as the
two of you stay crazy

1:06:32.589 --> 1:06:36.191
about each other, you
can handle anything.

1:06:38.762 --> 1:06:40.228
- I appreciate the advice.

1:06:40.263 --> 1:06:41.763
- I hope it helps.

1:06:42.866 --> 1:06:46.301
(amorous guitar music)

1:06:51.608 --> 1:06:56.378
♪ Are you lonesome tonight

1:06:56.413 --> 1:07:01.616
♪ Do you miss me tonight

1:07:02.686 --> 1:07:06.855
♪ Are you sorry
we drifted apart ♪

1:07:10.927 --> 1:07:15.263
♪ Does your memor stray

1:07:15.298 --> 1:07:18.967
♪ To a bright summer day

1:07:21.138 --> 1:07:21.970
- Dad?

1:07:22.773 --> 1:07:26.408
♪ And called you sweet love

1:07:26.443 --> 1:07:27.108
- [Laurel] Hey daddy.

1:07:27.144 --> 1:07:29.911
- Hey, sweetheart come on in.

1:07:33.884 --> 1:07:35.984
- So you wanted to talk?

1:07:36.953 --> 1:07:38.053
- Yeah.

1:07:40.724 --> 1:07:43.758
You want something to drink?
- Sure.

1:07:43.794 --> 1:07:45.660
- Got some water here
with fruit in it.

1:07:45.695 --> 1:07:47.462
Just have a seat.

1:07:47.497 --> 1:07:49.931
Hotel puts it in
here complimentary.

1:07:49.966 --> 1:07:52.100
- So, where is Isabelle.

1:07:52.135 --> 1:07:55.570
- She is downstairs
in the lobby eating

1:07:55.605 --> 1:07:59.007
a peanut butter and
banana sandwich.

1:07:59.042 --> 1:08:00.141
- Thank you.

1:08:01.778 --> 1:08:02.911
- So, I wanted.

1:08:04.581 --> 1:08:07.682
I just thought it
would be best if.

1:08:08.652 --> 1:08:11.719
Communication is
not my strong suit.

1:08:11.755 --> 1:08:14.923
- Your mother, she always
knew exactly what to say.

1:08:14.958 --> 1:08:19.094
She knew just what to
say, just what to do.

1:08:19.129 --> 1:08:21.229
You are so much
like her, you know.

1:08:21.264 --> 1:08:23.264
You got your talent from her.

1:08:23.300 --> 1:08:27.035
Your beautiful voice,
love of performing.

1:08:27.804 --> 1:08:30.839
She loved music
as much as you do.

1:08:30.874 --> 1:08:34.509
But all her hopes and
dreams and waiting

1:08:36.346 --> 1:08:40.281
for the luck that never
came hurt her deeply.

1:08:43.086 --> 1:08:47.021
And all I could do was
sit there and watch.

1:08:47.858 --> 1:08:52.026
And I just could bear to
see that happen to you.

1:08:53.530 --> 1:08:56.664
- That's why you didn't
come hear me sing?

1:08:56.700 --> 1:09:02.003
Why you were so determined for
me to go to business school?

1:09:02.539 --> 1:09:03.004
- Yeah.

1:09:04.674 --> 1:09:05.974
And I was wrong.

1:09:06.009 --> 1:09:09.077
- Dad, I love my
life and my job.

1:09:12.916 --> 1:09:14.983
And I love music too.

1:09:15.886 --> 1:09:18.052
Clay, he completes me.

1:09:21.825 --> 1:09:25.960
Can't there be room for
everything that makes me happy?

1:09:25.996 --> 1:09:27.195
- Absolutely.

1:09:31.368 --> 1:09:33.501
And I'm so sorry, honey.

1:09:34.638 --> 1:09:39.007
I've been a hindrance instead
of a help, but no more.

1:09:39.042 --> 1:09:44.012
You wanna sing, I'll be at
every single show from now on.

1:09:46.016 --> 1:09:48.016
You can depend on that.

1:09:48.818 --> 1:09:50.518
- I love you, daddy.

1:09:52.622 --> 1:09:56.224
- Oh, I love you too,
sweetheart, so much.

1:09:57.227 --> 1:09:58.193
- And Clay?

1:10:03.867 --> 1:10:06.067
- He's a good man.
- He is.

1:10:08.004 --> 1:10:10.638
- I might've been a
little hard on him.

1:10:10.674 --> 1:10:13.775
He can sure say how
much he loves you.

1:10:13.810 --> 1:10:14.676
And Emma.

1:10:15.812 --> 1:10:19.781
And if your momma was here,
I know just what she'd say.

1:10:19.816 --> 1:10:22.884
She'd say there is no
better man on this Earth

1:10:22.919 --> 1:10:24.652
for our baby girl.

1:10:25.655 --> 1:10:28.223
- Thank you, dad, thank you.

1:10:36.700 --> 1:10:38.266
- What are you doing here?
- What are you doing here?

1:10:38.301 --> 1:10:41.069
- I got a call.
- I got a call.

1:10:41.871 --> 1:10:43.605
- My parents wanted to talk.

1:10:43.640 --> 1:10:46.941
- My dad too, and he
wasn't the Major this time.

1:10:46.977 --> 1:10:48.109
He was dad.

1:10:50.580 --> 1:10:51.813
- Yeah, I don't know
what's going on.

1:10:51.848 --> 1:10:54.382
My mom's even rethinking
the whole doves thing.

1:10:54.417 --> 1:10:55.583
- And Isabelle's
agreed to compromise

1:10:55.619 --> 1:10:58.119
on decorations, it's weird.

1:10:59.923 --> 1:11:02.790
- So, you still wanna marry me?

1:11:03.526 --> 1:11:04.359
- Hmm.

1:11:06.096 --> 1:11:07.295
Absolutely.

1:11:11.768 --> 1:11:14.469
Wait, we still don't
have a minister.

1:11:14.504 --> 1:11:17.005
- I think I got that handled.

1:11:17.040 --> 1:11:20.208
- Hmm.
(Clay laughing)

1:11:25.682 --> 1:11:27.582
- Sunny day, clear skies.

1:11:27.617 --> 1:11:29.917
- It's because we buried
that bottle of bourbon.

1:11:29.953 --> 1:11:33.821
Never doubt your mom's old
Southern traditions, son.

1:11:33.857 --> 1:11:34.822
- Yes, sir.

1:11:36.359 --> 1:11:38.259
- I'm so proud of you.

1:11:40.830 --> 1:11:42.297
- Love you, pop.

1:11:45.969 --> 1:11:49.404
- Do I look all right,
the hair, the makeup?

1:11:49.439 --> 1:11:54.075
- The most gorgeous bride we
have ever seen, right Trish?

1:11:54.110 --> 1:11:56.444
- No argument here, ever again.

1:11:56.479 --> 1:11:58.313
- How do I look, mom?

1:11:59.182 --> 1:12:02.550
- Pretty as a picture,
come here baby.

1:12:03.720 --> 1:12:05.386
Beautiful.
- Thank you.

1:12:05.422 --> 1:12:07.121
- All right, now
there goes my makeup.

1:12:07.157 --> 1:12:10.792
- Okay, you two, we have to
get the finishing touches on.

1:12:10.827 --> 1:12:13.394
- All right, Miss Emma, let's
go on down to the chapel.

1:12:13.430 --> 1:12:15.063
See you in a little bit.

1:12:15.098 --> 1:12:16.331
Come on, hon.

1:12:19.469 --> 1:12:21.869
- I'm sorry, these
past couple of weeks

1:12:21.905 --> 1:12:23.604
have been so crazy.

1:12:23.640 --> 1:12:25.873
We really haven't had
much time to talk.

1:12:25.909 --> 1:12:27.141
- I'm the one who's sorry.

1:12:27.177 --> 1:12:27.842
- Isabelle?

1:12:27.877 --> 1:12:30.578
- I think I just wanted to help.

1:12:30.613 --> 1:12:33.314
To be a part of your life.

1:12:33.350 --> 1:12:36.484
- You are, forever,
we're family.

1:12:37.354 --> 1:12:39.220
- That's all I wanted.

1:12:39.255 --> 1:12:42.890
So, I wanted to lend you
something for your wedding,

1:12:42.926 --> 1:12:45.026
if you want it, that is.

1:12:46.363 --> 1:12:49.297
My mother wore this
at her wedding,

1:12:49.332 --> 1:12:51.866
and she always said
it brought her luck.

1:12:51.901 --> 1:12:56.371
So, if you don't already have
something borrowed or blue,

1:12:56.406 --> 1:12:59.774
I would be honored
if you would wear it.

1:12:59.809 --> 1:13:01.776
- I'd be so proud to.

1:13:01.811 --> 1:13:04.312
- I know I can never
replace your mother,

1:13:04.347 --> 1:13:06.414
and I wouldn't presume to try,

1:13:06.449 --> 1:13:10.618
but if you ever need
anything, I'm always here.

1:13:11.454 --> 1:13:13.321
Always ready to help.

1:13:13.356 --> 1:13:16.124
- You have no idea how
much that means to me,

1:13:16.159 --> 1:13:18.926
you truly don't.
- Oh, thank you.

1:13:23.166 --> 1:13:25.600
- You did remember to get
a minister, didn't you?

1:13:25.635 --> 1:13:27.135
- Oh, he's here.

1:13:29.873 --> 1:13:30.972
Good to see you, Chaplain.

1:13:31.007 --> 1:13:32.507
- Good to see you.
- Thanks for being here.

1:13:32.542 --> 1:13:34.075
- No, thank you.

1:13:34.110 --> 1:13:37.445
(gentle guitar music)

1:14:16.419 --> 1:14:19.754
- I love you, daddy.
- I love you too.

1:14:25.495 --> 1:14:26.694
- We made it.

1:14:27.664 --> 1:14:29.797
- Wow, you look amazing.

1:14:30.567 --> 1:14:32.467
- You don't look
too bad yourself.

1:14:32.502 --> 1:14:35.203
- You may be seated everyone.

1:14:37.307 --> 1:14:39.774
Friends, family, old and new,

1:14:41.244 --> 1:14:43.110
we're gathered here at
our beloved Graceland

1:14:43.146 --> 1:14:46.747
in this beautiful chapel
surrounded by the spirit of love

1:14:46.783 --> 1:14:49.917
to join together Laurel
Couper and Clay Sheppard

1:14:49.953 --> 1:14:51.819
in the bonds of holy matrimony.

1:14:51.855 --> 1:14:53.387
Now, I could go on
quite a while about

1:14:53.423 --> 1:14:55.623
what a perfect couple
these young people are,

1:14:55.658 --> 1:14:58.860
but Laurel and Clay asked
me to keep it simple,

1:14:58.895 --> 1:15:00.928
especially after the
last couple of weeks.

1:15:00.964 --> 1:15:03.664
(audience laughing)

1:15:03.700 --> 1:15:05.233
Now, at this point
in the service,

1:15:05.268 --> 1:15:07.635
I would like to turn it
over to Laurel and Clay,

1:15:07.670 --> 1:15:09.604
and the vows that
they have written.

1:15:09.639 --> 1:15:10.571
Clay?

1:15:10.607 --> 1:15:12.974
- Laurel, I knew how
special you were to me

1:15:13.009 --> 1:15:16.744
ever since the moment
you put gum in my hair.

1:15:16.779 --> 1:15:20.214
It was in third grade.
(laughing)

1:15:20.250 --> 1:15:24.919
I let you get away once and
fate brought you back to me,

1:15:24.954 --> 1:15:26.554
and I will never
let you go again.

1:15:26.589 --> 1:15:29.590
So from this day forth,
I will cheer you up

1:15:29.626 --> 1:15:30.725
in the bad times.

1:15:30.760 --> 1:15:33.261
I will celebrate
you in the good.

1:15:33.296 --> 1:15:36.998
And I will harmonize
with you when you sing.

1:15:37.033 --> 1:15:39.166
All the days of my life.

1:15:40.270 --> 1:15:41.702
It's your turn.

1:15:41.738 --> 1:15:44.839
- First, I gotta
say I was framed.

1:15:44.874 --> 1:15:47.975
It was Anna Mae Cowan
who put gum in your hair.

1:15:48.011 --> 1:15:49.510
Just to set the record straight.

1:15:49.546 --> 1:15:51.245
(laughing)

1:15:51.281 --> 1:15:55.283
Clay, you've always been
able to make me smile

1:15:55.985 --> 1:15:57.351
just by being there,

1:15:57.387 --> 1:16:02.690
whether it was at school,
backstage when I was nervous,

1:16:02.725 --> 1:16:04.225
or here right now.

1:16:05.461 --> 1:16:09.297
That's just one of
millions of reasons why

1:16:09.332 --> 1:16:12.733
I can't wait to spend
our life together.

1:16:13.703 --> 1:16:16.537
And we don't have time
for a million reasons,

1:16:16.573 --> 1:16:19.006
so let me just
give you one more.

1:16:19.042 --> 1:16:22.443
The simple fact is, I
love you, Clay Sheppard,

1:16:22.478 --> 1:16:24.712
always have, always will.

1:16:27.717 --> 1:16:29.817
- May we have the rings.

1:16:31.054 --> 1:16:32.653
- Thank you, Ted.

1:16:33.790 --> 1:16:35.189
- Now, if you'll repeat after--

1:16:35.224 --> 1:16:37.558
- If you don't mind, I
waited a long time for this,

1:16:37.594 --> 1:16:39.493
so let's just cut to the chase.

1:16:39.529 --> 1:16:40.394
I do.

1:16:41.831 --> 1:16:43.464
- And I do.

1:16:43.499 --> 1:16:45.666
- Well, that's that, then.

1:16:45.702 --> 1:16:48.069
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

1:16:48.104 --> 1:16:49.604
And you may now kiss the bride

1:16:49.639 --> 1:16:51.772
as I think they already
know, don't you?

1:16:51.808 --> 1:16:57.011
(applauding)
(dramatic orchestral music)

1:16:59.782 --> 1:17:04.118
♪ My lover my last
my everything ♪

1:17:11.194 --> 1:17:12.493
- You're good.

1:17:16.265 --> 1:17:18.899
♪ And loving with you are

1:17:18.935 --> 1:17:23.671
♪ I know there's only
only one of you ♪

1:17:23.706 --> 1:17:26.641
- Well, Ms. Sheppard, looks
like we pulled it off.

1:17:26.676 --> 1:17:29.410
- Took some doing, but I'd
say it's the perfect wedding.

1:17:29.445 --> 1:17:32.446
- Yeah, oh, and my mom's
planning our honeymoon.

1:17:32.482 --> 1:17:34.181
She had some great ideas.

1:17:34.217 --> 1:17:35.716
- Clay Sheppard.

1:17:38.855 --> 1:17:40.855
Would you look at that?

1:17:41.524 --> 1:17:43.557
- Never thought I'd see the day.

1:17:43.593 --> 1:17:44.692
- Me either.

1:17:53.069 --> 1:17:54.168
- Excuse me.

1:17:55.338 --> 1:17:58.739
Ladies and gentlemen, if I could
have your attention please.

1:17:58.775 --> 1:18:02.710
Everyone who knows
Laurel, knows that music

1:18:02.745 --> 1:18:07.815
has always been a huge
part of my daughter's life.

1:18:07.850 --> 1:18:09.483
It runs in the family.

1:18:09.519 --> 1:18:13.521
Most of the family, I couldn't
carry a tune in a bucket.

1:18:13.556 --> 1:18:17.458
And those of you who
know Clay, my son-in-law,

1:18:17.493 --> 1:18:20.261
know he's a pretty big
wheel in the music business.

1:18:20.296 --> 1:18:22.630
He was able to pull
just the right strings,

1:18:22.665 --> 1:18:24.699
and get just the right performer

1:18:24.734 --> 1:18:27.068
for this very, very
special evening.

1:18:27.103 --> 1:18:31.372
So, give a big Memphis
welcome to Mr. Lee Brice.

1:18:32.408 --> 1:18:34.341
- Lee Brice, are you kidding me?

1:18:34.377 --> 1:18:36.777
(cheering)

1:18:42.418 --> 1:18:44.752
- Thank y'all for
inviting me tonight.

1:18:44.787 --> 1:18:46.454
And for the happy couple.

1:18:46.489 --> 1:18:48.489
I'm so honored to be
here for the start

1:18:48.524 --> 1:18:51.859
of a beautiful road
to a happy marriage.

1:18:52.929 --> 1:18:56.230
(soothing guitar music)

1:19:00.670 --> 1:19:05.072
♪ Wise men say only
fools rush in ♪

1:19:15.551 --> 1:19:20.788
♪ But I can't help
falling in love with you ♪

1:19:30.867 --> 1:19:35.169
♪ Shall I stay
would it be a sin ♪

1:19:45.948 --> 1:19:51.085
♪ If I can't help falling
in love with you ♪

1:20:01.631 --> 1:20:06.834
♪ Like a river flow
surely to the sea ♪

1:20:09.005 --> 1:20:14.275
♪ Darling so it goes some
things are meant to be ♪

1:20:21.017 --> 1:20:26.120
♪ Take my hand

1:20:27.857 --> 1:20:32.960
♪ Take my whole life too

1:20:35.731 --> 1:20:40.968
♪ For I can't help
falling in love with you ♪

1:20:52.315 --> 1:20:54.949
Ladies and gentlemen, what you
say we invite up the couple

1:20:54.984 --> 1:20:57.785
to the stage and come help
me bring this thing home.

1:20:57.820 --> 1:21:00.054
- All right, then let's do it.

1:21:00.089 --> 1:21:02.256
(cheering)

1:21:04.093 --> 1:21:09.330
♪ Like a river flows
surely to the sea ♪

1:21:11.901 --> 1:21:15.970
♪ Darling so it goes

1:21:16.005 --> 1:21:21.175
♪ Some things are meant to be

1:21:23.479 --> 1:21:28.582
♪ Take my hand

1:21:30.319 --> 1:21:35.456
♪ Take my whole life too

1:21:38.594 --> 1:21:43.797
♪ For I can't help
falling in love with you ♪

1:21:53.876 --> 1:21:59.113
♪ For I can't help
falling in love with you ♪

1:22:14.897 --> 1:22:17.064
(cheering)

1:22:19.902 --> 1:22:21.802
- I thought we canceled this.

1:22:21.837 --> 1:22:24.638
- Honey, I couldn't
quit cold turkey.

1:22:24.674 --> 1:22:26.540
Don't you just love it?

1:22:26.575 --> 1:22:28.943
- I do, I do, I really do.

